title: no fail kringlas
directions: Mix and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours or overnight for easier rolling.
Roll 1 tablespoon of dough mixture
on flour covered pastry cloth to 8 to 10-inch long and the diameter of a pencil. Shape into bows on the cookie sheet.
Bake until brown.

title: bok choy oriental salad
directions: Toast sesame seed and almonds at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Mix cabbage after cutting in thin strips.
Stir in crushed noodles and scallions.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and chicken packet from noodles together.
Add nuts to cabbage.
Mix oil well and toss to noodles.

title: corn pudding
directions: In mixing bowl beat eggs slightly with a fork.
Add sugar, flour and salt together and add these to eggs; mix well.
Pour in corn, mix well.
Add milk and cooled butter, mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish, greased.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until set.
Serves 6 or 8. This recipe can be doubled.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add zucchini; mix well.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: wild apple relish
directions: Quarter unpeeled apples and remove core.
Grind apples in food grinder along with oranges and raisins.
Add sugar, cinnamon and vinegar.
Mix well.
Let stand at room temperature overnight. Refrigerate.
Keeps well up to 2 weeks.

title: baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breast halves in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, coated with cooking spray.
Combine tomatoes and remaining ingredients, stirring until well combined.
Spoon over chicken in dish.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until chicken is done. Yields 4 servings (1 chicken breast half with 1/4 sauce). Calories:
Exchanges:
2 lean meat; 1 vegetable.

title: banana split cake
directions: Step 1:
Combine the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 1 hour.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: *You can use ground beef also.

title: creamy fruit mold
directions: Beat cream cheese and gelatin.
Add water; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Refrigerate until thickened, about 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Add mayonnaise; whisk until smooth.
Stir in fruit and pecans.
Pour into a 1-quart mold sprayed with Pam.
Chill until firm.
Invert onto a serving platter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot cider
directions: Squeeze the juice from the lemons and oranges; set aside.
In a saucepan, add rinds, spices and water; bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Strain cooked mixture.
Add sugar, cider and juices.
Heat and serve.
Serves 16 to 20 cups.

title: sour cream herring salad
directions: Combine all and marinate for 24 hours.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs beating until blended.
Gradually add flour and cinnamon beating at low speed until blended.
Stir in oats, raisins and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: onion rings
directions: Beat good and dip onion slices in batter.
Have grease hot when you drop them in.
White onions are mild.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt overnight.
Drain.
In small bowl add remaining ingredients.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in
oil. Add garlic.
Cook until yellow.
Remove garlic.
Add soy sauce, salt and
1/4 c. water.
Cook slowly 45 minutes until beef is tender.
Add vegetables (not tomatoes). Cook until tender.
Stir corn starch into 1 cup water and thicken gravy.
Add tomatoes, cook 5 more minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: vegetable fish curry(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Heat 1 1/2 cups water and wine in large skillet over medium heat.
Add fish; cover and simmer 3 to 4 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Drain, reserving 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Heat corn oil over medium heat in large skillet.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes or until crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in reserved liquid.

title: gramp morse's gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding hot water last.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and add sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Magic Shell. Refrigerate.

title: potato pot pie
directions: Cook mushrooms and onions in 2 tablespoons dressing over medium-high heat.
Add flour and seasonings; gradually add milk, stirring until thickened.
Stir in 1 cup dressing, turkey, vegetables and 1 cup cheese; cook 5 minutes.
Spoon mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir 1/2 cup dressing into potatoes.
Top casserole with potato mixture; broil until golden.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; broil until cheese begins to melt.
Serves 6.

title: creamy mandarin salad
directions: Drain fruits well.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Beat eggs and blend with buttermilk.
Add flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Mix in oil and bran flakes.
Allow batter to set for 24 hours.
Can keep covered in refrigerator up to 6 weeks. Spoon into greased and paper lined muffin tins, about 3/4 full. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl; mix well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Press each ball with fork in crisscross design. Preheat oven to 325°. Bake for 12 minutes. Yield: 4 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin cobbler
directions: Cut butter into 4 pieces, and place in a 9 inch x 11 inch glass baking dish.	Place the dish in the oven to melt as oven preheats to 350°.
In a medium bowl, mix together flour, sugar, milk, and vanilla.	Remove dish from oven, and pour the flour mixture into the dish.
Set aside.	Break the eggs into a 2 quart mixing bowl.
Whisk the eggs.
Add the evaporated milk and pumpkin pie filling.
Stir slowly to mix well.
Pour or spoon the filling mixture on top of the reserved crust batter in the dish.
Do not stir.
The crust batter will rise to cover the pumpkin as it bakes.
Bake until the crust is dark golden brown on top, about 50 minutes.
Let the cobbler rest up to 1 hour before serving.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients, except Jell-O, in saucepan and cook until mixture thickens and clears.
Remove from heat; stir in Jell-O. Cool.

title: granny's corn light bread
directions: Heat shortening in an oblong or square baking pan that bread will be baked in.
Pour buttermilk into mixing bowl; add meal. Sift the flour, soda and salt into this; add sugar.
Stir well. Pour about half of hot shortening into batter; continue stirring until well mixed.
Pour batter into heated pan and cook at 350° to 375° for forty-five minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: sex in a pan(a.k.a. chocolate-caramel brownies)
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and half the milk.
Press half of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a double boiler, melt the caramels, adding the rest of the milk.
Pour half of the caramel syrup, half the nuts and half of the chips over the half baked chocolate cake. Form the rest of the chocolate dough into egg sized ball and place on top.
Now, pour on the rest of the caramel, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake for 18 minutes.
Enjoy warm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Combine chicken, chicken broth, Veg-All and soups in a bowl.

title: fluffy fruit salad dressing
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a small saucepan.
Gradually add pineapple
juice,
mixing
thoroughly.
Add
egg, stirring well. Place over	low
heat. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add marshmallows and stir until melted. Remove from heat and cool completely.
Fold in Cool Whip. Serve over fresh fruit.
Yields about 3 cups.

title: macaroni with eggplant
directions: Sprinkle eggplant with salt and let drain in a colander for 1 hour.
Pat dry.
Cook Prosciutto, garlic and eggplant in oil and butter over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the eggplant just turns golden.
Add the brandy and cook 30 seconds. Add the tomatoes, broth and oregano.
Simmer stirring occasionally for 30 minutes. Cook macaroni in boiling salted water al dente.
Drain. Toss macaroni with sauce in a large serving bowl. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: french apple cake
directions: Combine cooking oil, applesauce, sugar and eggs and beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Add to this mixture the flour, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in apples (peeled and cut into small pieces) and pecans.
Bake in cake pan, greased and floured for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, mixing well. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add to butter, sugar and eggs.
Add milk; mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1
1/2 hours.

title: easy popovers
directions: Grease 6 or 8 iron popover pan cups or custard cups.
Place the custard cups on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Place the popover pan or custard cups in refrigerator to chill.
In a medium mixing bowl, using a wooden spoon, stir together the flour, milk, eggs and salt until flour is moist (batter will be lumpy).
Pour the batter into pan 1/2 full.
Place pan in oven then set temperature at 400°. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: spiced mocha mix
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 1/2 cups mix.

title: flounder florentine
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Spread spinach evenly in ungreased rectangular pan, 11 x 7 x 2 inches. Arrange fish on spinach. Sprinkle with salt. Place bell peppers, basil, milk and pepper sauce in blender or food processor. Cover and blend on high speed about 15 seconds or until smooth; pour over fish.
Cover and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. This has 7 grams carbohydrates.

title: fettuccine with cream sauce
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo or butter.
Add flour and mix well. Add 1 cup whipping cream.
Mix with whisk.
Cook until thick.
Add grated Parmesan cheese.
Stir until melted.
Serve over fettuccine.

title: herbed croutons
directions: Mix cheese, oregano, garlic powder, basil, salt and pepper; set aside.
Toss bread cubes in a large bowl with the oil; then add cheese-herb mixture.
Toss thoroughly.
Spread on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° for 45 minutes to an hour, turning occasionally, until light golden and crisp.
Cool.
Store in plastic bags with tie or in jars with tight lids.
Will keep about one month.

title: easy casserole
directions: Fry turkey and add the remaining ingredients.
Place in a casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Combine sugars and milks with butter and salt in heavy saucepan.
Bring slowly to a full rolling boil over medium heat. Add the nuts and continue boiling until candy reaches the soft ball stage (234°) on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir only enough to give a creamy look.
Spoon out on wax paper or a buttered baking sheet.

title: german potato salad #2
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; peel and slice.
Cut bacon into small pieces and cook until almost done.
Add onions.
When the bacon and onions are done, add sugar.
Stir to avoid caramelization.
Add vinegar all at same time.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over potatoes and season with salt and pepper.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 15-inch pan with graham crackers. Reserve 1 cup crumbs.
Slice bananas crosswise into thirds and layer over graham crust.
Slice ice cream 1/2-inch thick; place over bananas.
Sprinkle peanuts over ice cream and freeze until hard.
Reserve.

title: white enchiladas
directions: Grate both cheeses together and put in bowl close to stove. Put small amounts of oleo in frying pan.
Put corn tortilla in to get it soft on both sides.
Put small amount of cheese mixture and onion in middle of tortilla.
Fold over and turn until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: tortilla pizzas
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 10 ingredients; mix well.
Place the tortillas on greased baking sheets; spread with cheese mixture. Bake at 400 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Cut into wedges.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: no fuss baked chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese and mustard in a small bowl.
Measure out 1/3 cup and refrigerate.
Brush both sides of chicken with the remaining mixture.
Coat well with crumbs.
Arrange in a lightly greased, shallow pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° until golden brown and tender, about 1/2 hour.
Serve with reserved mayonnaise for dipping.
Makes 4 servings.

title: applesauce
directions: Pare and quarter apples.
In a 2 1/2-quart glass casserole dish, combine apples and water.
Cover and cook for 7 to 9 minutes, or until fruit is soft, but not mushy.
Add sugar to taste and, if desired, press through colander or serve.
Season with cinnamon.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Refrigerate one day or overnight before serving.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, cook beef with salt and thyme, stirring occasionally until browned.
Drain juice into a small pitcher.
Stir flour and tomato juice into beef.
Beat eggs into warmed mashed potatoes until smooth.
Line bottom and sides of a 10-inch pie pan with 1/2 potato mixture.
Heaping up center, fill "crust" with meat mixture.
Spread remaining potato mixture on top, sealing around well.
Bake 30 minutes, then broil until top is golden brown.
Serve hot with reserved juice.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, mustard, onion, ketchup, and bar-be-que sauce together. Place mixture in a buttered baking dish. Cover mixture with brown sugar and then place bacon slices on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato chip dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Beat slightly with mixer.
Add sugar and salad dressing.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Let flavors marry and enjoy!

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
In a bowl, mix soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise together.
Stir in spinach, water chestnuts and onions.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: uncle frank's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix well in freezer can.
Add milk to fill line.
Freeze in ice cream maker according to freezer instructions.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan (ungreased).
Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: honey coconut balls
directions: Sift powdered sugar into a bowl and set aside.
Mix other ingredients into separate bowl.
Roll into balls and dip in powdered sugar.
Makes about 24.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Put all ingredients in a large crock-pot and cover.
Cook on High for 6 to 7 hours.
Uncover.
Cook 1 1/2 hours, until thick. Mix until desired consistency (lumpy or smooth).
Put into small containers.
Freezes well.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Combine eggs and milk, mixing very well.
Put cinnamon into mixture.
Cook in buttered, hot skillet until done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour; measure and sift with soda and salt.
Add bananas to creamed mixture.
Last, add flour mixture.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: torta rustica
directions: 1. Remove casing fron sausage and brown (crumble), and drain on paper towel. 2. Separate egg, mix yoke with ricotta cheese and basil or oregano.

Roll first pie crust to fit 9-inch pie plate. 3. Sprinkle 1/2 mozzarella, 1/2 sausage, all pimentos, all ricotta cheese mixture, then 1/2 sausage, 1/2 the mozzarella. 4. Roll second pie crust to fit top.
Use pastry brush to brush top of pie crust with egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cover with foil after 15 minutes if crust is getting too brown.

title: orange chicken oriental(weight watchers recipe)
directions: Place chicken on baking sheet; season both sides with salt, garlic and paprika.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until done. Transfer to large shallow casserole; set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine bouillon, water, orange juice, soy sauce, sweetener and thyme.
Bring mixture to boil; lower heat.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly; add dissolved cornstarch and cook until thickened.
Stir in orange rind.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving provides 6 P, 1/2 FR and 70 cal.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter until melted.
Add flour; stir until paste-like consistency.
Add 4 large eggs that are room temperature.
Drop dough onto cookie sheets about 1 tablespoon each.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes more or until browned lightly.
When cool, slice in half. Fill with whipped mixture.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Refrigerate, then serve.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal and pecans in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine in 2-cup microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir and microwave 1/2 to 1 1/2 minutes, until boiling.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on baking sheet to cool. Break into pieces.

title: gravy steak
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Sprinkle steak with tenderizer; let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle salt and garlic.
Place gravy mix and slices of butter on top of steak; wrap in aluminum foil. Bake for 25 minutes.
Reduce oven to 375° and bake for 1 hour or until tender.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour three 9-inch cake pans.

title: crisco single pie crust
directions: Spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Mix flour and salt in medium bowl.
Cut in Crisco with 2 knives until all flour is blended in to form pea size chunks.
Sprinkle with water, one tablespoon at a time.
Toss lightly with fork until dough will form a ball.
Press between hands to form 5 or 6-inch pancake. Flour rolling surface and rolling pin lightly.
Roll into circle large enough for pie pan and enough to flute the edges.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat until fluffy.
Add milk slowly while beating.
Add lemon juice and beat until creamy.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill several hours and then top with cherry pie filling.
You can also use blueberry pie filling in place of the cherry.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Cool.
Cream the margarine. Add sugars.
Add well beaten eggs and cooled oatmeal.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, floured and greased.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with Butter Frosting.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice bacon into small pieces and brown.
Saute onions with bacon.
Remove approximately 1/2 cup grease.
Combine vinegar and sugar in 1 bowl, water and cornstarch in another.
Boil potatoes until tender (do not overcook).
Cool, peel and slice.
Mix potatoes with bacon and onion mixture.
Pour liquid mixtures over potatoes; heat to thicken.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in a small amount of water; do not drain.
Add both cans of soup, milk, curry, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Heat all together; stir well.
I also add Velveeta cheese to mine.

title: creamy potato puffs
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and potatoes.
Mix until blended.
Add remaining ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scott's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except almonds.
Heat in microwave on High for 10 to 15 minutes until hot.
Sprinkle almonds on top and serve with crackers.

title: gamese
directions: Simmer together until vegetables are well done.
Test for salt.
Increase ingredients as desired for larger quantities.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello and water in 8 x 12-inch dish.
Stir in applesauce and box of frozen raspberries.
Float marshmallows on top.
Set in refrigerator.
Top with sour cream.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, peanuts and salt in 3-quart casserole on High for 9 minutes in microwave.
Add butter and vanilla; mix well and microwave for 1 more minute on High.
Stir in soda and pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: stacked cheese enchiladas
directions: In large saucepan, combine above ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes.

title: western beans
directions: Lightly fry bacon in a heavy, 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion; cook until transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cook over medium heat for 45 minutes, or until lentils are tender, stirring once or twice.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pork medallions with dijon mustard sauce
directions: Melt 2 teaspoons butter in medium skillet. Add shallot and mushrooms. Cook and stir 1 minute or until tender. Remove. Add remaining butter and oil to skillet. Add pork. Cook 8 to 10 minutes. Turn once. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Remove and keep warm. Gradually add apple juice. Stir in mustard and cream. Bring to boil. Boil 1 to 2 minutes. Add mushroom mixture. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Place pork on plate. Spoon sauce over. Garnish with thyme. Goes well with wild rice.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers very fine; add soft margarine, orange juice concentrate and confectioners sugar.
Work mixture into a dough by hand.
Form into a ball by the teaspoonful.
Roll balls lightly in coconut.
Chill overnight.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and butter.
Pour over cornflakes.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: sausage pies
directions: Prepare pie crust; set aside.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove stems from peppers.
Cut off bottoms and save.
Scoop out seeds.
Mix meat, rice, egg and seasonings.
Stuff peppers; replace bottoms and place peppers upright.
Add butter and a little water.
Cover and stew over medium heat until done.
Pour thick tomato sauce over peppers.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine first three ingredients and bring to a good boil. Add vanilla and soda after mixture has cooled slightly. Stir and pour over popcorn, coating evenly.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour in ungreased baking pan. Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all the above ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Spoon into pie crust.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serve chilled.

title: gizzadas(jamaican coconut tart)
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add water to make a stiff dough but work the dough as little as possible.
Roll out dough into 1/8-inch thickness, about 5 inches in diameter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Pinch edge between fingers to make the side about 3/4 inch high.
Fill with coconut mixture.

title: strawberry chicken salad
directions: Stir-fry chicken and season with lemon pepper seasoning. Cool.
Slice fruit in a festive manner.
Arrange chicken strips and fruit on a bed of spinach.
Sprinkle with cereal.
Drizzle salad dressing.
Contains 265 calories.

title: strawberry-amaretto trifle
directions: A day ahead, make tapioca pudding as follows:
Combine all pudding ingredients in saucepan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil (pudding thickens as it cools).
Remove from heat.
Put in refrigerator bowl and lay a piece of Saran Wrap on the pudding.
Refrigerate overnight!

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except French fried onions. Chill. Just before serving, fold in onions. Serve on lettuce. Serves 6.

title: cheesy zucchini casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 4.

title: fresh lemon sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir
until smooth, then cook over medium heat until thickened and smooth.
Stir constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until heated.
Serve over cake or nut bread.
Yield:
about 1 2/3 cups.

title: hard-boiled egg casserole
directions: Saute onions and butter until tender. Add flour and milk. Stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Layer 1/2 of sliced eggs in a greased casserole dish.
Pour on 1/2 of the sauce.
Top with 1/2 of the potato chips and 1/2 of the bacon.
Repeat, ending with bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with fresh fruit and muffins.

title: date cherry loaf
directions: Combine dates, cherries, water with juice and baking soda.
Set aside.
Cream sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add flour and date mixture alternately.
Line loaf pan with waxed paper and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: millet loaf(serves 5)
directions: Whiz onion in blender, using small amount of tomato juice. Then mix everything in.
Pour into a baking dish treated with thin layer of lecithin.

title: macaroni buffet skillet
directions: In a large skillet, cook onions, garlic, green pepper and ground beef in vegetable oil, stirring until meat is broken up and loses its red color.
Add uncooked macaroni, corn, tomatoes, salt, pepper, cheese (from package) and water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes, or until macaroni is cooked.
Stir frequently.
Makes four servings.

title: homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl; add remaining ingredients, stirring to mix.
Pour mixture into a 1-gallon ice cream freezer and freeze.
Let ripen 1 hour.

title: martabak telor(indonesian egg-onion crepe)
directions: Ingredients such as fish sauce, tamarind paste, black bean paste and pickled radishes are essential to the flavor of the dish and cannot be left out without adversely affecting the flavor.
All are available in neighborhood Oriental shops or can be made by hand with dried tamarind, home pickled radishes, etc.

title: whipped cream salad
directions: Dip banana slices in pineapple juice.
Whip cream until stiff. Fold in fruits, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Serves 8.

title: easy quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, milk and seasoning.
Toss cheese with flour.
Add cheese and cooked bacon to egg mixture. Add optionals if you wish.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco.
Gradually add sugar. Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa together.
Add alternately with the milk, starting and ending with the dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour large tube pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well potatoes, sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla or lemon and milk. Pour into uncooked pie crust. Dab a little butter on top. Cook until done.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Store in a tightly covered jar in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: eve's chicken
directions: Shake up chicken in seasoned flour and brown in butter. Sprinkle Marsala over the chicken in the pan and remove the chicken from the pan.
Add tomato paste to the pan with a bit more flour, then add the bouillon and stir until the mixture thickens. Add sour cream with a whisk and stir until smooth.
Then add currant jelly and salt and pepper (the amount of these will depend upon how highly seasoned your bouillon was) and 1 tablespoon of cheese.
Replace the chicken in the mixture and cook for 20 to 30 minutes over moderate heat.
Sprinkle with remaining tablespoon of cheese and brown under broiler.
If you cook this in the oven, instead of on top of the stove, do so at 350° for about 45 minutes.
It is most convenient of all to cook it in an electric skillet.
This recipe is for 6.

title: microwave chocolate pecan pie
directions: Place margarine in 4-cup glass measure. Microwave on HIGH for 1 minute. Blend in sugar, flour and eggs. Add chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Rotate twice during baking. Microwave on 50% power (MEDIUM) for 10 to 11 minutes or until set. Bake in conventional oven for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan, add carrot, onion, salt, celery salt, pepper, milk and potatoes.
Cook stirring constantly for 20 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 30 minutes or until top of brownies turn light brown and edges start coming away from side. Cut while hot.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients into pumpkin in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in Pet milk.
Stir in milk; mix well.
Fill pie crust full.
Bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.
(Put top pies on bottom rack of oven and bottom pies on top rack of oven.)
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Makes 4 pies.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet.
Drain fat.
Add tomato soup, green beans, salt and pepper and cook on medium until thoroughly heated.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish and place biscuits on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: punch
directions: Mix juices and ginger ale together with ice to suit taste. Pour into punch bowl.
Float ice cream in punch.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Flour chicken and brown in butter.
Combine other ingredients. Pour half over rice prepared according to box directions.
Lay chicken on top and pour remainder of liquid over the chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or longer.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix together and shape into balls, about 1 tablespoon in each ball.
Melt 6 ounces semi-sweet chocolate chips and 1/4 block of paraffin in double boiler.
Dip candy.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients except pie crust, adding nut meats last.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in hot oven (450°) 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and continue baking until a silver knife blade inserted comes out clean.

title: butter toffee popcorn
directions: Boil butter, sugar and Karo for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add soda and stir.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir to coat and bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir once during baking.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Whip first 3 ingredients together until stiff, put into refrigerator.
Whip cream cheese and sugar together, add to first mixture and whip.
Put into graham cracker pie crust.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Pour this mixture over the sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana-nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 24 muffin cups or use paper liners.
Beat together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Beat in bananas until smooth.
Mix together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Alternately stir in flour mixture and buttermilk into egg mixture until just moistened.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spoon into pans, filling cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until golden.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Keeps for years.
Delicious served over cream cheese with Ritz crackers or as a ham sauce.
Clears your sinuses!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
In a 3-quart saucepan, heat water until boiling.
Add vinegar and macaroni; cook until tender.
Add macaroni to hamburger and spaghetti sauce. Simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally to avoid sticking. Sprinkle cheese on top and serve.

title: curried soup
directions: Cook 10 to 15 minutes. Will stick to pot. Serves 6.

title: southern pineapple ade
directions: Combine Kool-Aid and 3 quarts water; add juice.
Pour over ice in large punch bowl.
Add Sprite before serving.

title: pretzel salad(sounds awful, but is very good!)
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press in bottom.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, Cool Whip and 3/4 cup sugar.
Spread over cooled pretzels.
Dissolve jello in water. Add frozen strawberries.
Let set partially.
Pour over cream cheese.
Refrigerate about 2 hours or overnight.
Serves 12 to 15. Festive looking for Christmas.

title: creamy pina colada
directions: In blender container or mixing bowl, combine sherbets and pina colada concentrate; blend until smooth.
Stir in rum.
Place in airtight container.
Freeze 1 to 2 hours or until slushy.

title: loaf bread
directions: Mix dry yeast in water and dissolve.
Add milk, butter, salt and sugar.	Stir
well.
Add flour in small amounts (save 1/2 cup)
and
mix
thoroughly.
The
dough
will
be
stiff. Sprinkle some flour on a dry surface.
Knead dough until it is smooth. Place dough
in
a	greased bowl, cover and set aside for 1 hour. Punch
dough
down	and
shape
into a small oval roll.
Place
in a greased loaf pan.
Cover and set aside for 35 minutes.
Bake in	loaf
pan
in
the
Dutch
oven
for 35 minutes.
Set
aside to cool for five minutes and then invert loaf pan and remove.

title: blackberry or raspberry jam cake
directions: Cream together 2/3 cup of butter and 1 1/2 cup sugar. Separate 3 egg yolks, reserving the whites.
Slightly beat the yolks and mix with 1 cup of jam; whip into creamed mixture.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, ground cloves and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients alternately with 1 cup sour milk. Beat the 3 egg whites and fold into the batter.
Add vanilla. Bake in 3 lined layer cake pans in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Test with a toothpick.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting or a vanilla frosting.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs or chips.
Cook for 15 or 20 minutes.
Put cracker crumbs on top and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.
May be made ahead of time and cooked just before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a buttered baking dish; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Combine margarine, flour and brown sugar; spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are soft and topping is golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Beat egg whites.
Set aside.
Beat yolks with juice and sugar until thick and lemon color.
Beat in flour and baking powder. Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Cook butter, brown sugar and pineapple until sugar dissolves.
Put this mixture in 10 inch cake pan.
Pour batter on top of this.
Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees. Use water and vanilla if you don't have pineapple juice.
Turn upside down and cool when done.

title: rich egg bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, eggs, margarine and 3 1/2 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine milk, vanilla and butter; add flour, salt, 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa, sifted together.
Beat until smooth. Stir in nuts.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix 1 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa and sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yields 10 servings.

title: peach delight
directions: Pour can of peaches in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour dry cake mix over peaches.
Add melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
It will not get real brown. Don't overbake.

title: grit casserole
directions: Cook grits in salted water until done.
Add oleo, cheese, green chilies, pimiento and eggs.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: gourmet meat loaf (wellington)
directions: Bring ground beef, veal and pork to room temperature and combine.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Saute onion and garlic in oil until onion is translucent.
Set aside.
Add bread crumbs to meat, then add onion-garlic mixture, parsley, cognac, egg, salt, pepper, allspice, and thyme.
Blend well with each addition.
Press mixture into prepared loaf pan and top with bacon.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from oven; let stand 20 to 30 minutes; drain pan.
Raise oven heat to 425°.
Wrap loaf in pastry; brush lightly with water and cut 1-inch slits every 2 inches across the top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Remove from oven; let stand for 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: homemade chocolate-covered cherries
directions: Drain and freeze cherries overnight on a flat surface.
Mix sugar, vanilla, milk and margarine into a dough.
Place a cherry in a small piece of dough and roll into a ball.
Place them in freezer for 20 minutes.
Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Dip cherries in melted chocolate.
Drain excess and place on waxed paper.
Best when made about 2 weeks in advance and stored at room temperature.
The inside becomes syrupy just like those store-bought cherries.
Makes 70 pieces.

title: ora mabry's crusty pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and flour, beating after each addition.
Batter is stiff.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: green beans and mushrooms
directions: Saute onion in oil until transparent.
Add beans, pimento, parsley and mushrooms.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fry together lightly to heat through.
Serves 4.

title: cherry pie filling salad
directions: Combine pie filling, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. Once blended well, add pineapple, pecans and marshmallows. Mix well and chill to serve.

title: orange sherbet mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix the lemon jello into the hot water.
Stir until the jello is dissolved.
Cool just until syrupy, then add the orange sherbet and stir until melted.
Stir in the oranges (drained) and the walnuts.
Pour the mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or glass dish.
Chill until set.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour.
Add milk gradually.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add salt.
Melt cheese in cream sauce.
Cook cabbage in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Alternate layers of cabbage and cream sauce in a greased baking dish.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in blueberries. Place in well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hawaiian splendor sponge cake
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add undrained crushed pineapple and eggs. Stir thoroughly until combined.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place on a cooling rack for 10 minutes. Spread Golden Frosting over cake in pan.

title: fluffy turnips
directions: Cook cubed turnips in
water
to
cover
until	tender; drain and mash.
Beat egg yolks
and
combine with the rest of the ingredients except egg
whites
and
sugar.
Beat
whites until soft peaks form;
gently fold into turnip mixture.	Pour into buttered casserole dish
and
sprinkle
with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crystal fruit glaze
directions: Cook apple jelly in pan on low heat until liquid.
Increase heat until it begins to boil.
Remove and pour onto pound cake, fresh fruit, waffles or white cake or any dessert that can be cooled.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Cook sausage, bacon and hamburger.
Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients, except croutons.
Cut bacon in pieces before adding. Put in enough croutons to desired consistency.
Stuff in turkey or bake in pan at 350° until warm.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: In a microwavable 3 quart dish, combine margarine, brown sugar and Karo syrup.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring halfway through.
Stir in soda.
Place popped popcorn in brown paper bag. Pour brown sugar mixture over popcorn.
Stir or shake to coat popcorn.
Put bag in microwave and cook on High 1 minute.
Stir. Cook on High another minute.
Shake and serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and hot water until syrupy, then cool. Add jello and cool.
Fill a baked pie shell with ripe strawberries. Pour strawberry glaze over the strawberries.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat in egg. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased 8-inch square pan in a moderate oven for 20 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool or serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Spread pie filling smoothly into oiled pan.
In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend in softened butter and egg, stirring to make a thick batter.
Drop batter from spoon to cover pie filling.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until apples are bubbly and topping is brown. Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.
(May use blueberry, cherry or blackberry filling.)

title: mexican panocha
directions: Combine chocolate, brown sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil.
Add butter and stir occasionally until candy reaches soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts, mixing until candy begins to harden.
Turn into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cut into 2 dozen squares.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups warm water in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover bowl tightly.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Spoon dough into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be stored in refrigerator 3 or 4 days. Yield:
2 dozen.

title: stuffed eggplant rolls
directions: Wash eggplant and thinly slice lengthwise.
Beat egg.
Dip eggplant into egg then both sides into bread crumbs.
Heat broiler. Add several tablespoons oil to 4-sided cookie sheet (to cover bottom).
Heat sheet in broiler.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour a 10-inch 12-cup Bundt pan. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa; set aside. In a large bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add flour mixture alternately with milk; mix well. Pour into Bundt pan. Bake for 70 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into cake comes out clean. Let cool for 10 minutes in the pan, then turn onto a wire rack and cool completely.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and set in fridge overnight in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
The next morning, heat oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer as listed above.
(Then 2 cups of real mayonnaise, try 1 cup first, 1 Tbsp. sugar mixed.)
Dot over top of salad and spread to the sides.
Then top with shredded cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with American style croutons and extra bacon bits if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and soda.
In another bowl, combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat vigorously until frothy. Add bananas and blend thoroughly.
Fold into flour mixture until blended.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until crust is brown.
Use a toothpick to test for doneness. Remove pan to a rack; let stand 10 minutes.
Invert pan; cut into 1-inch slices.

title: shrimp commodore
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter 2 minutes.
Stir flour then water.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Add seasonings.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Blend in tomato juice.
Add shrimp and heat thoroughly, about 5 minutes.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Stir all ingredients over medium heat until syrupy mixture coats nuts and leaves the side of the pan.
Put on a baking sheet and bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir once.

title: red cabbage
directions: Clean and chop red cabbage.
Heat oil in large pan over medium heat and add cabbage and onion.
Stir to coat cabbage.
Add about 1/2 to 1/3 cups water and 2 to 3 tablespoons vinegar.
Add the apples and spices; stir.
Cover to let steam 70 to 90 minutes. Taste for salt, sugar and more vinegar.

title: 4 minute fudge(microwave)
directions: Place sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in a glass mixing bowl. Do not mix.
Microwave on High or Full power for 4 minutes.
Mix well and stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla and nuts.
Pour into lightly buttered 8 x 8-inch dish and refrigerate for 10 minutes.

title: jarrett anderson tartar's pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate eight hours or overnight.

title: spanish rice crock-pot style
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot, stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours or on high 3 hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil until tender.
Set onion and green pepper aside.
Mix salt, black pepper and flour.
Then roll with beef.
Pound steak with edge of a heavy plate.
Brown meat on both sides in oil.
Put in baking dish and add all remaining ingredients. Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients (except chicken) in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Put chicken wings into pan and pour marinade over wings.
Marinate at least 24 hours in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yellow squash-zucchini dip
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in butter in a Dutch oven until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until blended and thoroughly heated.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cut up celery and cook in saucepan with water until tender. Remove from stove and pour off water; add chestnuts, chicken soup and melted butter.
Stir and place in a casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and almonds.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea tomato soup
directions: Soak black-eyed peas overnight.
Rinse with cold water.
Cook in 4 cups cold water until tender for approximately 10 minutes. Saute onions in oil.
Combine rest of ingredients (add parsley last) and simmer in saucepan until carrots are tender.

title: ranch chicken casserole
directions: Tear tortillas in small pieces.
Heat the soups and broth together (you may also heat the tomatoes and chilies with the soup).
Then begin to arrange ingredients in layers as well as liquid ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Thaw fruit.
In small bowl microwave cream cheese for 30 seconds or until softened.
Combine all ingredients and blend until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit slices.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a microwave-safe pan. Sprinkle oil and your choice of herbs.
Microwave 10 minutes on High.
Rearrange potatoes after 5 minutes.
Let rest 5 minutes and microwave another 6 minutes.
Add cheeses.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: hominy bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together (reserve 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese for top) and put in casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together in a large mixing bowl.
Chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fruit slush
directions: Prepare juice as directed on cans.
Stir in sugar, pineapple and strawberries.
Stir.
Freeze 1 hour.
Makes 20 servings.

title: sorghum sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening; let cool.
Add sugar, sorghum and eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Mix well and chill.
Form into 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet or these will burn.
Greased sheet must be greased thoroughly.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook & drain spaghetti.
Put in bottom of 9x13 in. dish.
Add meat and then sauce.
Combine half cheddar and mozzarella and put on top of sauce.
Add soup.
Bake in a 375 degree oven for approximately 35 minutes.
Add remainder of cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: pizza corn dog snacks
directions: Remove stick from each corn dog; cut into 1 inch slices. Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Spread with pizza sauce. Top with olives, mushrooms and cheese. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.

title: grandma k's red cabbage
directions: Add a small amount of water to first 3 ingredients and boil until tender.
When done, add remaining ingredients and simmer for a few minutes.
You may add a little flour to thicken.

title: catalina cheese dip
directions: Blend ingredients together and chill.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, vanilla and oleo, then mix in sugar and wafers.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on wax paper lined baking sheet and chill. Dip in dipping chocolate or melt the chocolate chips and paraffin.

title: herb pinwheel rolls
directions: Generously grease a large bowl and 10-inch round baking pan. Sprinkle yeast over warm water in large bowl; let stand until proofed and foamy, about 10 minutes.
Stir in milk, sugar and salt.
Add 2 cups of flour; beat well.
Add 1 more cup of flour; mix thoroughly.

Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead in remaining flour until dough is smooth and satiny, about 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl, turning to coat entire surface. Cover; let rise in warm area until doubled, 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit filled cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; sift flour, soda and salt and add together (this is awfully thick).
Add oats and work in with hands to a thick mixture.
Divide in half.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Rub pan with shortening.
Crumble 1/2 evenly over pan, then pat down. Next, cut up real fine dates and mix with sugar and enough water to moisten.
Cook this over fire until thick; let cool.
Spread dates evenly over mixture, then crumble rest over top.

title: angel rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a bowl; let stand 5 minutes. Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine oil, buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened. (Dough will be sticky.)
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter. Place rolls on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 16 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: oatmeal apple crisp
directions: In ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine 1/2 of crumbled cookies, apples, dates, sugar, orange juice and butter.
Blend remaining cookies with nuts.
Sprinkle over apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well; add oil.
Sift soda, baking powder and flour.
Mix well; add zucchini and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: ranch swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into 6 pieces and pound the flour into meat.
Brown well in shortening.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add garlic and onion.
Continue cooking until the onion is tender and browned. Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Bake in 375° oven until meat is tender, about 2 hours.

title: dijon dill sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Great with salmon or other fish.

title: coffee tapioca
directions: Cook to desired consistency.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, horseradish and cheese with 1/2 cup dried beef.
Refrigerate at least 15 minutes for easier handling.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining dried beef. Refrigerate at least 20 minutes before serving.
Makes a 4-inch ball.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash and cover cucumbers in cold water; let stand overnight. Drain and pack in jars. Put in large saucepan the vinegar, salt and water. Bring to a boil. Pour over the cucumbers. Add to each jar 1 or 2 dill sprigs. Seal jars.

title: chow chow
directions: Let cabbage, peppers, onions and green tomatoes set 1 hour after grinding.
Bring to a boil remaining ingredients.
Add the vegetables and let simmer for 3 minutes. Put in jars while hot.

title: spicy lime chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for 5 hours or overnight.
In blender, chop onion with garlic, wine, lime juice, cilantro, sugar, chili powder, cumin and salt. Blend until onion is finely chopped.
To marinate; place chicken in food storage bag, pour onion mixture over chicken, shake to coat all pieces of chicken.
Refrigerate for 5 hours or overnight.

title: low-low-fat chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes.
Add fresh fruit for a topping if desired, i.e., kiwi, strawberries.
Less than 5 grams of fat for entire cake.

title: christmas wassail
directions: At Christmastime, this is a favorite of my family.

title: oatmeal applesauce cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: clam balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Prepare Stove Top as directed on box.
Pat stuffing mix on bottom of baking dish.
Cook broccoli and cauliflower until cooked half done and still crunchy.
Combine soup and vegetables.
Spread on top of stuffing.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: coffee frappe
directions: Put ice cream into blender.
Add other ingredients to blender and blend for 2 to 4 minutes or until foam forms on top.

title: deviled ham stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolks and set whites aside. In a small bowl, mash yolks with fork. Add next 8 ingredients. Mix well. Stuff into egg whites. Refrigerate until serving. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: skillet cabbage creole
directions: Melt corn oil in a large skillet.
Pour vegetables into pan. Sprinkle
salt
and
sugar on top of ingredients.
Cover and cook over
medium
heat for 10 to 12 minutes.
Vegetables will be crisp,
just
as
good
the next day, if there are any left. Serves 6 to 8.

title: day after thanksgiving casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions. Stir cranberry and nuts into stuffing. In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, spoon stuffing. Arrange turkey pieces on top of stuffing. Pour gravy over turkey. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot. Serves 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples into a 13 x 9 dish. Sprinkle remaining ingredients. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Blend the bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper. Combine melted butter and garlic.
Dip chicken into butter, then into crumb mixture, coating thoroughly.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Drizzle lemon juice and any remaining butter over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mochiko chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and soak overnight.
Deep fry in oil or bake.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until thickened.
Add milk, whipping cream, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Add to ice cream freezer.
Turn until machine stops.

title: country omelet
directions: Cook sausage or bacon and onion until done.
Pour eggs, seasoned with salt and pepper into a skillet.
As eggs are cooking on low heat, crumble sausage or bacon and add to eggs along with onion and grated cheese.
Cook until eggs are done and cheese is melted.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
and
serve as a dip with crackers.
(Tastes like crab dip, a good fooler.)

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put zucchini and onions in food processor and chop fine.
Mix with salt and place large bowl.
Cover with cold water and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Drain, rinse and drain.
In 6-quart pan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a quick boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until reduced to 3 quarts.
Place in jars.
Then apply a hot water bath.

title: crabmeat casserole(serves 10)
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 300°.
Mix all together (except stuffing) and place on casserole dish.
You can place stuffing mix on top of mixture.
Then bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and instant pudding well.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in large casserole dish. Chill.

title: grandma's nut bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Now mix everything together.
Add 1 egg white, beaten stiff; fold in.
Allow to raise 20 minutes.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Makes 2 loaves.

title: spinach cheese balls
directions: Cook spinach; drain until very dry.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Roll balls in palm of hand to the size of an egg yolk.
Place in pan and freeze.
When ready to use, set out and thaw for 5 minutes before placing them on a lightly greased tin. Bake at 325°
for 25 minutes.

title: raggedy ann salad
directions: Place carrot peels in ice water so that they will curl (for hair).
Use 1/2 pear for face and cloves for eyes and nose.
Use 1/2 tomato, decorated with mayonnaise for bodice.
Place scoop of chicken, lobster, crabmeat, etc., salad under full leaf of lettuce for skirt.
Use 2 gherkin pickles for legs.
Use 2 whole green beans for arms.
Use a piece of tomato skin for mouth or pimento.

title: melted-chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a microwave oven or over simmering water.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
Stir to blend.
In a medium-size mixing bowl, beat margarine and fructose until smooth.
Beat in vanilla and egg.
Continue beating at least 2 more minutes.
Add melted chips and beat well, then gradually beat in flour mixture.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Spray Pam inside sack.
Pour popcorn into sack.
Melt margarine in a 4 cup measuring cup.
Stir first 4 ingredients together.
Cook 2 minutes on High after mixture starts to boil. Remove from microwave; add soda and stir well (foamy).
Pour syrup over popped corn in paper sack.
Fold down sack top twice.
Cook sack and all 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Loosen sack and shake like crazy.
Repeat steps.
Put in bowl (hot).

title: kona kahlua liquor
directions: Mix together coffee, sugar and boiling water.
Let cool.
Mix with brandy and vanilla bean.
Store in 1 gallon glass jar for at least 4 weeks.
Shake occasionally.
The longer it sits the better it gets!

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Boil 1/2 bag egg noodles until tender.
Drain.
Combine beef, noodles and soup in casserole dish.
Mix well.
Put 1/2 bag of cheese in mixture.
Mix well.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Heat thoroughly in oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add flour, sugar and salt and mix well. Add drained corn, then liquid.
Finally, add melted butter and bake in a casserole at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating between each egg. Add other ingredients alternating with buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until done and golden.
Ovens may vary.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Grease large cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix in pan; cut up margarine and place on top. Cream softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs. Pour on top mix. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: tomato-cheese pie
directions: Lay sliced tomatoes on bottom of pie crust.
Mix together the mayonnaise and cheeses.
Fill pie shell with mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: easy green bean casserole
directions: Drain 4 cans greens beans; place in casserole dish.
Mix cans of soup together with drained green beans.
Add 1 cup Cheddar cheese and mix together with beans and soup.
Place 1 cup of grated cheese on top of dish.
Add French onions, almonds or bacon bits. Use all 3 if you like.
Place in oven on 350° for 45 minutes (can be microwaved).

title: chili
directions: Brown beef lightly.
Add onions and cook until onions are clear, but not brown, drain.
Add 1/2 puree and liquid; simmer until beef is tender.
Make a paste of flour and water, add to beef mixture, stirring constantly.
Add beans and seasonings.
Cover and cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours until flavors are well blended and mixture is thickened, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: carrots in galliano
directions: Slice carrots into thin slices.
In heavy saucepan, melt butter and stir in the Galliano and spices.
Stir in the carrot slices and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon water.
Cover and simmer over low heat 5 minutes.
Turn the heat on high.
Remove the lid and continue to cook carrots 15 minutes, until liquid is absorbed. Serves 8.

title: fudge walnut brownie pielolly's favorite!
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 inch pie pan.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt; stir into butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into prepared pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Garnish with whipped cream of serve with a big scoop of BlueBell.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushroom caps and dip in melted butter.
Arrange on a greased cookie sheet, cap side up.
Combine remaining ingredients except cheese and mix lightly.
Fill mushrooms with crab mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: oyster chowder
directions: Cut up potatoes into chunks.
Leave skin on potatoes.
Boil until almost soft.
Fry bacon and crumble into potatoes.
Don't drain all of the water from potatoes.
Add 1 can evaporated milk. 1 can oysters, salt, pepper, hot sauce and paprika along with onions.
Simmer until onions are soft.

title: chicken and mushrooms(can be made up to 24 hours in advance)
directions: Combine 1/4 cup flour, paprika, 1 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Halve breasts; coat with flour mixture.
Brown in butter.
Add 2 tablespoons water; simmer, covered, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove chicken to a 2-quart baking dish (11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch).
Reserve drippings in skillet.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and cream.
Stir into reserved drippings in skillet.
Add mushroom soup.
Stir and cook until thick and bubbly.
Drain mushrooms; add mushrooms and lemon juice to sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Cover.
Chill up to 24 hours.
Bake, covered, at 350° until hot, 50 to 60 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until cheese melts, 1 to 2 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a bowl, mix the bread crumbs and seasoning packet of stuffing mix with the melted butter and stir.
Cook zucchini and onion together in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Combine chicken soup, sour cream and carrots.
Stir in the onions and zucchini.
Put half of the stuffing mix into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour in the zucchini mixtures and top with the remaining stuffing.
Bake, covered, for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover for the last 5 minutes.

title: cheese dip or sandwich spread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 250° for approximately 20 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
(It's great for sandwiches.)

title: baked fudge
directions: Beat the eggs and then add the sugar.
Cut the chocolate into pieces and put it and the milk or water in a small saucepan.
Stir and cook over a low heat until a smooth thick paste is formed. Cool the chocolate paste and then add it to the egg mixture.

title: pumpkin streusel muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; set aside. In a medium bowl, combine the eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Sprinkle streusel topping over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 18 muffins.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine the flour, salt, baking powder and sugar. Add the remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon in hot oil like doughnuts. Serve with honey or jam.

title: wieners, beans and biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients, except biscuits and chips in ovenproof skillet and simmer 5 minutes.
Separate biscuits and dip top of biscuit in 1 tablespoon melted butter and then dip into chips; place over mixture in skillet.
Repeat with other biscuits.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes (or until biscuits are golden brown) at 350°.

title: candy cane oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Shape into candy canes.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix jello, orange juice, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Shake thoroughly.

title: plum good cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.
May sprinkle sugar over top.

title: cheesecake
directions: Press crackers, sugar and butter into 9 x 9 inch pan. Beat eggs, vanilla, cheese and sugar until smooth and pour over crust. Bake in 350 degree oven for 25 minutes. Let cool. Top with blueberry or cherry pie mix.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
Add salt and pepper, if desired. Add Ragu sauce to hamburger and simmer a few minutes.
Cook noodles as directed.
Spoon some sauce on bottom of pan to prevent noodles from sticking.
Arrange 3 noodles in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 pound Mozzarella on noodles, then 1/2 pound Ricotta and 1/2 the hamburger sauce.
Layer 3 more noodles and repeat layers of cheeses and sauce (save 2 to 3 tablespoons of sauce for top).
Place 3 noodles on top.
Spread the remaining sauce on last noodles.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, until hot and bubbling throughout.

title: easy potato cheese soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and stir while warming. Serve with a sprinkle of grated cheddar cheese on top.
Yield: 2-3 servings.

title: carne asada(mexican steak)
directions: Combine ingredients in a plastic bag placed in a bowl to catch drips.
Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours.
Remove steak from marinade. Broil 2 to 9-inches from heat source about 5 minutes each side. Slice very thinly against the grain.
Makes 4 servings under 170 calories each.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch uncooked pie shell
Bake at 350° until solid and brown.

title: french fried onion rings(thinner fritter batter)
directions: Put egg whites into small bowl.
Beat until stiff but not dry. Mix egg yolks and milk in large bowl.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add to milk mixture.
Beat on medium speed until blended, scraping bowl while beating.
Beat in butter and lemon juice.
Add beaten egg whites and gently fold in, only until blended.
Batter can be used for onion, green tomatoes or artichoke hearts.

title: just delicious cookies
directions: Mix sugars,
oil,
oleo, egg and flavorings.
Add soda, cream of	tartar	and flour.
Then add Rice Krispies, coconut, oatmeal and nuts.
May bake immediately or store in refrigerator until needed.

title: tasty meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix ground chuck with soup mix.
Add bread crumbs softened with milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Put in loaf pan and shape.
Spread catsup over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove from oven and pour excess fat off.
Cool and slice. Makes 10 to 12 slices.

title: cheese soup
directions: Finely chop (with processor) onion, celery and carrots and saute in butter.
Add soup, broth and cheese.
Cook and then add the sour cream before serving.
(This freezes well without the sour cream.)

title: luscious layers
directions: Mix together butter, flour and nuts.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Cool. Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding with cold milk. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours.
Top with Cool Whip and chocolate curls or nuts.
Keep in refrigerator. Recipe is also called "Sex in the Pan".

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together and stir in flour, salt and cocoa. Bring coffee to boil.
Add soda at once.
Pour over batter while still fizzing.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, drain.
Slice potatoes, salt and pepper them. Place ground beef in baking dish; add layer of potatoes; alternate layers.
Put onion on top.
Combine milk and soup, pour on top. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: cocoa chip chews
directions: Crumb together shortening, brown sugar and flour and press into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
While that is baking, stir in with well beaten eggs the next 5 ingredients.
Then mix in coconut and chocolate chips. Spread on baked crust.
Bake for 25 minutes until golden brown. Cool and cut.

title: holiday cake
directions: *Use the different jellos for special holidays, i.e., green for St.
Patrick's Day, yellow for Easter, orange for Halloween and red for Christmas.

title: antoinetta paglione's apple cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar first, then add the rest of the ingredients in order given.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured well.
Cake is done when toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: best brownies in town
directions: Mix together in order given; mix after each ingredient.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
I double this and make 2 pans, one for now and one for the freezer for later.

title: jamie's chocolate mousse pie
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler or carefully on stove or in microwave.
Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla.

title: best fruit cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Cream well until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a
time;
mix well.	Sift flour and baking powder together. Chop nuts	and fruit and mix with some flour.
Fold in flour mixture
with
butter mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts; mix
well.	Fold
in
nuts	and
fruit.
Pour
into greased, paper-lined tube
cake
pan.
Place
in cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours or until done.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: In a bowl, stir together cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder. Mix all ingredients well. In a separate bowl, beat eggs and stir in milk. Add liquid mixture to cornmeal mixture and stir in remaining ingredients. Pour batter into 2 well-greased and preheated baking pans and bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pork chops with applesauce gravy
directions: Using a large heavy skillet, brown pork chops in oil; drain off excess fat. Combine gravy mix, applesauce, water, honey, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and ginger.
Pour over pork chops. Cover tightly and simmer 50 to 60 minutes or until pork is tender. Stir gravy once or twice during cooking period.
Serve with white rice or egg noodles.
Serves 6.

title: tamale pie
directions: Fry onion in oleo until tender.
Add meat and saute until brown and crumbly.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Put mixture into a greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish and cover with corn bread mixture (mix as directed).
Bake at 350° until corn bread is done.

title: southern seafood salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in small mixing bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers or as a sandwich.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Heat Mexican Meat and 2/3 of tomato juice in large saucepan. In separate pan, prepare Roni-Mac noodles per package directions. When noodles are done, drain and add to meat mixture.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add more tomato juice if desired.
Serve with side dish of corn, hot rolls or corn bread.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix well Crisco, sugar and egg; add milk.
Sift in flour.
Mix in nuts and fruit.
Chill dough about 1 hour.
Drop cookies on greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together; make out into 1 1/2-inch balls. Put in ungreased skillet; brown all over.
Takes about 10 minutes; pour off fat.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; then add sugar and potato flakes.
Set out all day in a warm spot.
Now refrigerate for 3 to 5 days.
Put in quart or 1/2 gallon jar.
After 3 to 5 days, feed the starter with 3/4 cup sugar, 1 cup warm water and 3 tablespoons potato flakes.
Set it out all day; then pour 1 cup to make bread. Put the rest in refrigerator.

title: easter bunny salad
directions: Place 1/2 pear (round side up) on lettuce leaf.
Use marshmallow for tail.
Place 2 almonds for ears.
Place mints or jelly beans under pear for rabbit eggs.

title: holiday dessert pizza
directions: Press dough onto a 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned and puffed.
Cool completely. Beat cream cheese, sugar, orange peel and vanilla until blended. Spread over cookie.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese.
Brush with jam.
Serves 12.

title: great beef hot pot
directions: Place 1/3 of the potato slices in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole; top with even layers of half of the ground beef, onion slices, cabbage and carrot slices.
Sprinkle with part of marjoram, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers, ending with potato slices arranged in a pattern on top.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with parsley.
Pour beef broth over all; cover casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: war cake (world war i)
directions: Boil first 9 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Add preserves, then add baking powder and the flour to make a stiff batter.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: fruit salad
directions: Bananas, cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Apple, cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Set aside cherries and nuts.
Mix all of the ingredients. Sprinkle cherries and nuts on top.
Chill for about 1 hour.

title: souper burgers
directions: Brown beef and drain; add soup and catsup to beef mixture. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Just before serving, add cheese and stir until blended in.
Serve on buns.

title: charleston red rice
directions: Fry bacon, remove from pan.
Saute onions in grease.
Add tomato paste, water, salt, sugar and pepper.
Cook uncovered slowly (about 10 minutes) until it measures about 2 cups.
Pour into the top of a rice steamer with the rice.
Add extra bacon grease if desired.

title: sugar-free jello salad
directions: Cook pineapple juices and jello for 2 minutes (add no water). Cool, then add other ingredients.
Other flavor of jello may be used.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: First remove stem and cut off top of artichoke to make flat. Use scissors to remove any remaining tips on leaves.
Rinse under cold water while spreading leaves slightly.
Turn upside down to drain.
Mix breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese and garlic together. Using spoon, stuff in between each leaf completely stuffing the artichoke.
Place about 1 1/2 inches of water covering bottom of pot.
Add lemon juice.
Place artichokes in pot with cover.
Pour 1 teaspoon of oil on top of each artichoke.
Bring to a boil, then simmer about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Check to make sure water has not evaporated.
Enjoy!

title: georgie's bean salad
directions: You may vary recipe with cauliflower, broccoli, young zucchini, yellow squash, radishes or any and all of these raw vegetables (all are good in this salad).

title: pat's strawberry angel food cake
directions: Cook 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Then add Jell-O.
Let cool and add strawberries to mixture.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and 3/4 cup sugar.
Spread in between layers and on top. Pour strawberry mixture over this.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and Hidden Valley together until blended well.
Stir in rest of ingredients (except flour tortillas).
Mix well.
Lay out shells.
Spread mix.
Roll shells and wrap tightly. Chill for 2 hours.
Cut off roll ends and slice into 1-inch slices.

title: lemon blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cold water and lemon juice.
Stir in pie filling.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Fold sugar into sour cream until blended.
Spread over jello.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Crushed pineapple can also be added to jello (drained).

title: chilly cottage cheese mold(a light and refreshing way to enjoy cottage cheese.)
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over pineapple juice.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Cook juice over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Combine juice, cottage cheese and strawberries in blender or food processor until smooth.
Turn into a 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm; unmold onto salad greens.
May garnish with a few fresh strawberries and mint leaves.
To serve, cut 2-inch slices and place on a bed of salad greens.

title: company roast
directions: Mix and pack all ingredients except the water-Sovex mixture and butter
in well-oiled loaf pans (2).
Pour hot water with Sovex and butter over roast.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions, celery and pepper.
Cook until done. Add all other ingredients, except cheese, and mix well.
Put in baking dish and bake about 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and continue baking until cheese melts.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oats in boiling water for 20 minutes. Beat butter until creamy. Gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy. Blend in vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add oat mixture. Mix well. Sift flour with salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Mix into oatmeal mixture. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Frost cake in pan.

title: chicken honolulu style
directions: Split chicken in quarters.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour in bowl and marinate about 2 or 3 hours.
Drain chicken and bake for 1 1/2 hours for small quantity (for 2 hours if larger quantity or until done).
Brush now and then with marinade.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, minus 1 stick butter.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut up 6 to 8 pieces of bread, melt the other stick of butter in skillet and add bread cubes to melted butter.
