When bread has soaked up butter, put it on top when the rest is almost done, so it doesn't get too brown.

title: impossible apple pie
directions: Place sliced apples on the bottom of a greased pie plate (Pam spray okay).
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Melt stick of margarine.
Remove from stove; add 1 cup of sugar, flour, egg and vanilla; mix.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Combine butter, sugar, flour and milk in blender; blend.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Add peaches; do not stir.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: raspberry cooler(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Combine sugar, mint leaves and water in a 2-quart casserole. Cook on High for 2 1/2 to 4 minutes or until mixture boils.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add frozen raspberries and limeade.
Stir until raspberries are thawed. Gradually stir in club soda, just before serving.
Serve on ice.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown meat in oil until done; drain.
Add water, onion, celery and spaghetti sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Line the skillet with noodles, cover with lid and cook over low heat.
When noodles are done, add cheese.
Cook until all cheese has melted; salt and pepper to taste.
Layer the cheese on top of meat and noodles.
It is ready when all cheese melts.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans (about 2 1/2 cups batter in each pan).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.

title: perfect dill pickles
directions: Pack cukes in jars with lots of dill.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar to each quart, garlic and/or hot peppers.
Combine water, vinegar and salt; boil for 10 minutes.
Pour boiling brine over cukes. Fill to tops of jars and seal.
Set the jars in boiling water to come to tops of jars.
Let stand until cool.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and chopped onion fine.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating between each.
Sift together dry ingredients, adding alternately with milk.
Last, add flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in sugar and flour which have been mixed together.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked crust and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beet soup(borscht)
directions: Cook beets, skins on, until tender, approximately 1 hour. Remove skins when cooled.
Peel potatoes; cube and boil until done in 2 cups water.
Salt to taste.
Grate beets (using large holes on the grater).
Add beets to potatoes; simmer 10 minutes combined. Into a cup, put sour cream, flour and vinegar.
Mix until smooth, approximately 2 tablespoons broth may be added.
Pour sour cream mixture into soup.
Bring to boiling point, but do not boil.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Melt
marshmallows
in	1 cup water.
Pour over Jell-O. Let congeal in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Take out and beat until all bubbles are gone.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts. Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients with a fork.
In separate dish, beat remaining ingredients.
Stir into flour mixture until moistened. Mold into ball.
Chill before rolling.

title: easy pleasing meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, stuffing mix, 1 cup water, eggs and 1/4 cup of barbecue sauce. Shape meat mixture into oval loaf in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; top with remaining 1/4 cup barbecue sauce. Bake at 375° for at least an hour or until center is no longer pink. Makes 6 to 8 servings. Enjoy!
tags: Stove Top homestyle herb stuffing mix

title: quick barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add catsup, tomato sauce and vinegar.
Mix together.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: paper bag chicken
directions: Rub whole chicken with vegetable oil; then sprinkle with a mixture of the remaining ingredients (mixed all together in a small bowl).
Coat the inside of a large heavy brown grocery bag with 1/4 cup cooking oil.
Lay bag in a large shallow baking pan with the seam side up; fold the open end of the bag over and fasten with a large paper clip.
Bake at
325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: gazpacho(cold mexican soup)
directions: Use food processor to chop vegetables.
Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: one cheese ball
directions: Beat together at room temperature.
Chill overnight or until stiff enough to handle.
Form into a ball by rolling in Saran Wrap, then roll in walnuts.
Wrap in Saran Wrap, then aluminum foil, then freeze.
(I make about 5 small balls.)

title: kahlua chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes in a well-greased and floured Bundt pan, or 3 greased, floured layer pans.
A light glaze may be put on Bundt cake. Layers, frost as desired.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine melted margarine and dry cake mix.
Reserve 1 cup of this for top crust.
Put remaining crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top that layer with combined peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme and spread evenly.
Crumble remaining cake mixture over that.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix cauliflower, onion and bacon together.
Combine sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour evenly over cauliflower mixture.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle cheese over top of mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix just before serving.

title: butter bean pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In large Pyrex dish, put in one pie crust, like you would for a deep dish pie.
Add a layer of ground beef, a layer of butter beans and a layer of sliced onions. Cover this with ketchup.
Repeat this to the top of the dish. With the last layer, add water with ketchup to fill completely to the top of bowl.
Put top layer of crust and crimp crust together on sides.
Cook at 350° until crust is brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.	Brown onion and green pepper in bacon grease until tender.
Mix all ingredients together.
Crumble bacon and mix onion and green pepper, including grease, all together with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a medium saucepan, heat milk until small bubbles form on side of pan and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast to milk and stir until dissolved.
In a large bowl, cream butter, salt and shortening; gradually add sugar and honey.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Gradually add flour, alternating with milk mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Beat for 2 or 3 minutes after final addition.
Place in a greased bowl; cover with a tea towel and allow to rise in a warm place 1 hour or until double in bulk.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours or until chilled.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream. Then fold in sour cream. Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until done (test with a clean toothpick). Serves 12.

title: shrimp cocktail dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and grated onion or onion powder.
Mix well and spread on tray or plate.
Pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese mixture to cover.
Top with drained shrimp.
Serve with assorted crackers or vegetable dippers.

title: italian pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add vanilla, then flour.
Press with pizzelle iron.
Cook until golden brown.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix and shape in balls; layer in pan single.

title: crisscross casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add seasonings and other ingredients.
Boil.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place narrow slices of American cheese on top in a crisscross fashion.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: oriental chicken tartlets
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Bake the chicken breast on parchment lined baking sheet for 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Let cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes about 30 minutes, then mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Whip cream cheese with the sugar, sour cream and vanilla. When mixed well, add Cool Whip.
Pour in shell and let set for 1 hour.
Spread canned pie filling or fresh sweetened fruit on top or add 2 tablespoons on each slice when serving. Makes 1 very full pie or two medium filled crusts.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender, not brown.
Add meat, onion, soups and rice together and mix.
Put in casserole dish and top with dressing, mixed according to package directions.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a bowl, except the whipped topping.
Then fold in the topping and pour into the 2 crusts. Chill no less than 1 hour.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed.
Pour milk over cake while warm. Punch holes in cake so milk can go down in it.
Let cool.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Crush Heath bars and sprinkle over top of Cool Whip.

title: seasoned chicken
directions: Skin meat and put in ungreased square pan.
Spread 1 teaspoon butter on each piece; sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes, until tender.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve. Serves 4.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix well and pour into well greased bundt pan.
Bake one hour at 325 degrees.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes and turn onto cake plate.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: five minute trifle
directions: In bowl whisk milk and pudding for 2 minutes.
Let stand until soft gel set.
Cut cake into 1 inch cubes.
Place in a 2 quart glass bowl.
Top with berries and pudding 2 quart glass bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Garnish with whipped topping and additional berries.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Form into balls; brown.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Add carrots, potatoes, mushrooms and onion in casserole dish and microwave for ten minutes.
Drain.
In baking dish, put chopped cooked chicken at bottom of dish.
Add vegetables.
Spread mushroom soup over mixture.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with one package of stuffing mix and one-half cup melted butter or margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: pureed carrots and potatoes
directions: Cook carrots with pinch of salt and sugar for about 15 minutes or until tender.
Cut potatoes in even pieces and boil with a pinch of salt until tender. Drain vegetables and then place together in deep pot over low heat.
Using an electric mixer, blend in the milk and butter.
Add nutmeg, salt and pepper to taste. Whip until fluffy.
Place in warm bowl and garnish with parsley.

title: sunday chicken
directions: In bowl, combine soups, butter and rice.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces over mixture. Brush with remaining butter; season with salt and pepper and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings; may freeze.

title: jewish meat loaf
directions: Mix all together (except soup, mushrooms and 1/2 cup milk). Put in pan.
Mix soup, mushrooms and 1/2 cup milk.
Spread on top of meat loaf and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare cake mix according to directions on box and pour over coconut pecan mixture.
Place margarine and cream cheese in saucepan.
Heat until warm enough to stir in powdered sugar. Spoon over cake mix.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut when cold.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in a bowl, mixing well.
Combine 1 cup nonfat buttermilk with soda.
Add to banana, eggs and oil. Pour all liquid ingredients into dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter onto griddle sprayed with Pam. Makes 12 pancakes (4-inch size).

title: congealed peach salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot water.
Add cold water.
Mix in cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Stir into gelatin.	Fold in Cool Whip and peaches.
Pour into 8 inch x 8 inch glass dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix the powdered sugar, coconut, graham cracker crumbs, butter, salt, peanut butter and vanilla.
Form into balls (about 1-inch in diameter).
Melt the chocolate and paraffin together in a double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper. Chill until firm.

title: chocolate caramels
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and cook 5 minutes. Add chocolate and milk. Stir until chocolate melts.

Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (238°). Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Pour mixture into a buttered 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle with almonds. Cover and chill overnight. Cut into squares. Store in refrigerator.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: surprise stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, saute the summer squash and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from the heat, stir in remaining ingredients.
Transfer to a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and Cheddar as directed on package for oven method, except use 2 1/4 cups water.
Stir in tuna, green pepper and olives.
Cover; bake 20 minutes.
Blend butter and garlic powder; stir in croutons.
Stir casserole and sprinkle croutons over top.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shirley's chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and eggs.
Add cocoa and gradually beat in powdered sugar.
Add vanilla.
Frosts 4 layers.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients and put aside.
Pour half of cake batter into cake pan and bake 15 minutes.
Remove cake from oven and pour caramel mixture over top.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts. Pour remaining batter over top and return to oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 20 minutes before serving.
Can use two 9 x 9-inch pans and put one in freezer.
Can use ice cream or whipped topping.

title: cabbage supreme
directions: Put cabbage in shallow 4-quart casserole.
Pour milk over cabbage.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes or until nice and brown.

title: date and nut meringues
directions: Add salt to egg whites.
Beat to a stiff foam. Add sugar, sifted with flour, one tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until dry and stiff. Fold in nut meats and dates.
Add vanilla. Drop from teaspoon on aluminum foil or unwaxed paper, 1/2 teaspoon in rounds. Bake in slow oven at 300° for 25 minutes. Turn over aluminum foil and cool.
Peel off. Store in tin box.
Yields over 2 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in the 2 cups of boiling water until tender; drain.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in mayonnaise, onion, green pepper, cheese, salt and pepper.
Fold in zucchini.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Take 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine and add bread crumbs until it resembles topping. Sprinkle over zucchini mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white buttercream frosting
directions: Beat sugar, butter and vanilla until fluffy.
Gradually beat in cream.
Beat 5 minutes until smooth.

title: meaty minestrone
directions: Wash kidney beans and put them in Dutch oven.
Add water and bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour. Drain tomatoes into beans reserving tomatoes.
Add meat, cabbage, carrots, onion, garlic, basil and pepper to beans.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and turn down heat.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Cut reserved tomatoes into pieces.
Add tomatoes, macaroni and green beans to soup and simmer 15 minutes or until macaroni and beans are tender.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: vegetarian omelet
directions: Put the vegetables and the bouillon cube in 1 cup water in large skillet (frypan).
Put lid on and cook until the water evaporates.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1/2 cup of margarine in an oblong pan.
Stir in brown sugar; spread evenly in pan.
Drain pineapple; reserve syrup. Arrange pineapple in pan.
Add cherries inside the pineapple.

title: chili relleno appetizers
directions: Layer cheese and chilies on bottom of a 9-inch
square pan. In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk and flour.
Pour over cheese and chilies.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cook chicken, drain and cut up.
Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch chips.
Mix soups, sour cream, olives, chilies and onion.
Fold in chicken. Grease baking dish.
Layer chips, chicken mix, more chips, then cheese.
Continue making layers, ending with cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: country-fried steak with cream gravy
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Pound meat to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin; cut into 10 to 12 serving size pieces.
Place in a large bowl; add water to cover.
Stir in 1 tablespoon salt and vinegar.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 2 hours.

title: cheesecake de jean
directions: Brownies: Follow box directions and let them cool. Cook in serving dish or cut and place in another dish. Blend the cream cheese, powdered sugar and sour cream with a blender until smooth and soft. Add the milk, one cup at a time. If the milk is room temperature, it will not lump the cream cheese mixture. Add instant pudding directly into the mixture and mix until smooth. Spoon this mixture over the brownies. Top with the cherry or blueberry pie filling.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Mix the cocoa, sugar, milk and butter; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter, oats and coconut to the cocoa mixture; stir well.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Let set until firm, then add big glass of milk.
Eat and enjoy.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Brown sausage, onion, pepper and garlic.
Combine all ingredients in a soup pot and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: jim dandies
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together.
Cream the next 3 ingredients together.
Stir into creamed mixture half dry ingredients.
Add cherry juice and milk.
Add rest of flour. Blend in chocolate (use unsweetened chocolate squares only, not cocoa), pecans and cherries.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
While still warm, spoon on marshmallow cream and cool.
Frost with icing.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Steam eggplant in water 1/2 hour.
Drain and mash.
Add egg, mushrooms, cheese and seasoning.
Add bread crumbs to make firm patties.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour and cocoa in bowl.
In another bowl, cream oil and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add food coloring.
Mix until well blended.
Combine buttermilk and soda. Mix well.
Add to oil-sugar mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in three round 8-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Combine milk and remaining sugar in saucepan; bring to boil.
Spoon over layers when done.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar together in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze overnight.

title: hash brown-potato casserole
directions: Place thawed hash browns in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together next 7 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed cornflakes and drizzle melted oleo over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: captain john's crab stew
directions: Saute bacon in a large heavy saucepan.
When bacon is crisp, remove from pan and set aside.
Cook potatoes and onions in bacon grease until golden brown.
Add Worcestershire sauce, water, salt and celery salt; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir frequently. Add crab meat, half and half, milk and hot sauce and simmer for an additional 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Additional milk may be needed if stew gets too thick.
Serve in large bowls; top with cracker pepper and chopped parsley.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together sauerkraut, celery, pepper, onion and pimento. Melt sugar in warm vinegar and while still warm, add oil.
Pour over sauerkraut mixture and pat down well.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: holiday ripple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed using high altitude directions.
Cool several hours or overnight.
Slice in 3 layers.
Mix pudding using 1 1/2 cups milk.
Let stand until thick.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Over medium to high heat, put cooked pork and cooked rice into skillet or wok.
Mix up.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except beaten eggs.
Once mixture is heated, add eggs and mix until eggs are cooked.

title: aunt el's cheesecake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating on high.
Put half the salt, vanilla, cornstarch and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add remaining half until well mixed.
Grease a 9 x 3 3/4-inch spring-form pan with butter or margarine.
Line pan with 1/2 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave for an additional hour with oven door closed.

title: smoked wild turkey
directions: Bring your smoker to heat.
Add some green or soaked hickory or oak wood.
I use green pecan.
Put turkey in smoker.
Adjust heat to about 170°.
Smoke 1 1/2 hours for each pound of turkey. Baste every 30 minutes with bacon drippings.
Try to keep temperature between 160° and 180°.

title: jimmie's favorite cabbage relish
directions: Use a large dishpan to chop cabbage in.
Bring vinegar, sugar and salt to boil in large pan.
Add peppers, cabbage and onion. Bring back to boil for about 5 minutes.
Have about 8 to 10 quart jars and lids hot and ready to fill.

title: shrimp fra diavalo
directions: Lightly saute the olive oil, onion and garlic cloves.
Add tomatoes, mushroom pieces and stems, sugar, oregano, basil, crushed red pepper and water.
Add cooked shrimp and warm thoroughly. Serve over linguini.

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well and refrigerate overnite.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and spread over crust.
Mix instant chocolate pudding and spread over 2nd layer.
Spread more Cool Whip on top of pudding. Refrigerate.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Add crushed pineapple to pan before cooking cake.
Pour cake mix over the pineapple and then bake.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Combine margarine, honey, mustard and curry powder.
Baste chicken every 15 minutes until chicken is tender.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: fresh citrus cooler(spa drink)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a pitcher; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add chilled sparkling water; stir well.
Serve immediately over ice.
Garnish with lime, if desired.

title: sweet-soy marinade
directions: In plastic bag or nonporous bowl, mix all ingredients and combine with 1 1/4 pounds of beef strips or pork strips or 2 pounds of chicken pieces.
Marinate beef or pork up to 24 hours; chicken 2 to 4 hours.
Thread beef or pork strips on bamboo skewers that have been soaked in water.
Grill or broil.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: pizzo-macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni.
Beat milk, egg, 1 tablespoon grated cheese and salt.
Blend into cooked macaroni and spread in greased 11 x 13-inch pan.

title: buttermilk corn cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients and add eggs, mixing lightly until lemon colored.
Add milk and cheese to egg yolks.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture. Cook at once on a hot greased griddle.
Serve with sliced strawberries, honey or maple syrup.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients until just combined.
Batter will be thick.
Spread evenly in pan.
Cook for 1 hour or until done.

title: one foot in the fire fudge cake
directions: Combine water and chocolate.
Cook over low heat; stir constantly until melted.
Remove from heat and cool.
Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Start and end with mixture.
Add chocolate mixture and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 19 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on racks.
Spread with fluffy white filling between layers. Chocolate on top and sides.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix pudding with some of the juice from pineapple.
Next add pineapple, then sour cream.
Blend well by hand.
Add Cool Whip last.
Pour into baked pie shell. Refrigerate.
Can be made in advance.

title: low-fat seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add crab flakes and vegetables.
Stir over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add seasoning.
Cook 1 minute.
Garnish with chow mein noodles.
Serve immediately. Serves 3.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate onion, then grate potatoes.
Add salt, flour and egg. Mix well and fry in Crisco.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread coconut and nuts in pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour batter over coconut and pecans.

title: salmon salad
directions: Soak gelatin in milk.
Dissolve in hot milk.
Add remaining ingredients and place in a well-oiled mold.
Crab meat or shrimp may be used in place of the salmon.
Serve with salad dressing.

title: chunky apple cake
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients in a large bowl until well blended. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients. Add to butter mixture, stirring until well blended. Stir in apple slices and nuts. Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely in pan on a wire rack. Spread with a cream cheese frosting.

title: pineapple squiggle squares
directions: Add pineapple chunks to strawberry gelatin.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares.

title: ox roast
directions: Brown meat in oleo.
Put meat and other ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 16 to 18 hours.
Tear meat with fork and place on buns or eat as is.
Can add barbecue sauce for sandwiches also.

title: no-fuss zesty potato soup
directions: Clean and prepare potatoes for cooking. Cook potatoes until tender. Drain and reserve potato water in bowl. Slightly mash potatoes and return to saucepan. Add all the other ingredients except flour and cheese. Cook on low heat (be careful not to scorch milk). Take 1 cup of the reserved potato water and mix in 1 tablespoon flour for thickening. Add slowly to your saucepan, stirring constantly. Let simmer about 10 minutes. (If soup is too thick, you can add a little more of the potato water.) Remove from heat and add grated cheese. Serve.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Mix
sugar,
cornstarch
and water; heat slowly to dissolve sugar.
Add
3/4 cup of the berries; boil for 5 minutes, until mixture is thickened and clear.
Remove from heat.	Stir in remaining
berries;
mix
well.
Pour
into crust.	Chill. Top with Cool Whip.

title: crustless cranberry pie
directions: Adding ingredients in the order given is important.
Put cranberries in a deep 10-inch greased pie plate.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over the berries.
Spread nuts on top.
Beat eggs.
Add 1 cup of sugar and beat.
Add flour and beat very well.
Add butter and shortening.
Beat well again.
Pour over cranberries in pie plate.
Preheat oven for 1 hour.
Bake at 325°.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped topping.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix 1 cube butter (melted) with cracker crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, vanilla, 2 cubes butter and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Beat 15 minutes (no less).
Pour over cracker crust.
Slice bananas and place over mixture.
Put drained pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts and garnish with cherries.
Put in refrigerator and let set overnight or put in freezer for 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Stir cheese and macaroni into boiling water and cook for 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add butter.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Grate cheese on top and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix and stir all the ingredients except the browned margarine.
Stir in the cooled, browned margarine last.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and then at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Butter baking dish.
Add fruit.
Mix oatmeal, flour, salt, sugar, cinnamon and margarine until like crumbs.
Place on top of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Thoroughly cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg and molasses. Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until smooth. Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes. Stir 2 times while cooking.
Chill and serve.
Do not double the recipe.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix everything together.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli; combine crumbs and melted oleo.
In buttered casserole put broccoli, cheese, seasonings and crumbs by layers, crumbs on top.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy penuche icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk.
Bring to boil stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add confectioners sugar.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add flour and sugars until well blended.
Beat in butter.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 60 minutes at 325°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix soup and chicken in small pan on the stove.
Add salt. If too thick, add 2 tablespoons of milk.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes on low heat.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries; add the sugar and let stand overnight. Next morning, add the pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Mix well, then fold in the whipped cream.
Chill well before serving.

title: yeast doughnuts
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Work down and roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Fry in hot oil. Drain well.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: hamburger impossible pie
directions: Fry hamburger, onion, salt and pepper until lightly browned. Grease 9-inch glass pie plate.
Pat hamburger in bottom.
Put cheese over hamburger.
Mix well remaining ingredients.
Pour over hamburger and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: raspberry topped lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, combine berries and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and is clear.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks, stir in Eagle Brand, lemon juice and yellow food coloring, if desired.
Pour into crust. Bake 8 minutes.
Spoon raspberry mixture evenly over top.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in a large bowl. Mix well.
Place in well greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until lightly browned and firm.
Serve hot. Refrigerate leftovers.
Yields 6 to 8 side dish servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: salisbury venison steaks
directions: In a large bowl combine first 10 ingredients.
Mix well; shape into 10 patties.
Thoroughly coat each patty with flour.
Heat 1/3 cup oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add patties and brown on both sides.
Transfer patties to a greased roasting pan.
Place onion and mushrooms over meat.
Add remaining tablespoon of oil to drippings in skillet.
Stir in 2 tablespoons flour and cook over medium heat until flour begins to brown.
Stirring constantly, add beef broth and cook until slightly thickened. Pour gravy over steaks.
Cover and bake one hour at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs. Mix together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Blend the two mixtures together. Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts. Prepare a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon and roll each ball into the mixture. Place the balls 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oriental rice
directions: Break sausage apart and combine next three ingredients. Simmer until tender.
Add water chestnuts and pimentos.
Boil 3 cups water and add whole box (2 packages) of dry chicken soup. Remove from heat and add Minute rice.
Combine sausage mixture and soup mixture together and put into casserole dish and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: von's tomato bisque
directions: Peel the Tomatoes.
Simmer or stew until well cooked.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Add milk to required consistency. Season and enjoy.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt Crisco.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, then vanilla and powdered sugar and mix well. Pour into 8 x 8-inch (ungreased) baking dish.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 64 squares.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, then place all ingredients listed into crock-pot.
Heat to boiling, then simmer all day or overnight.
Serve.
Makes approximately 6 1/2 large soup bowls. Diabetic exchanges:
1 cup = 1 starch, 1 ounce meat and 1 fat.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine over low heat, stirring constantly.
Mix sugar and crushed cereal in large bowl.
Pour melted peanut butter mixture over cereal and mix well.
Form into small balls with fingers.
Place in freezer about 15 minutes. Melt almond bark in microwave oven.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper to harden.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed to desired tenderness.
Cool.
Dice all vegetables and add to cooked noodles.
Sprinkle Good Seasons dressing on noodles.
Add Italian dressing and olive oil.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: coconut chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix the powdered sugar and shortening. Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake until golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread over baked layer.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool. Frost with Orange Lemon Frosting, if desired.
It's good without frosting.
Cut into bars.

title: chicken en bianco
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with oil and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°; drain.
Melt 1 stick oleomargarine and simmer peppers and mushrooms until slightly soft, about 10 minutes.
Put mushrooms and peppers on chicken breasts. Pour the margarine and juice over chicken breasts.
Pour the Sauterne over all and cover tightly with foil if not serving immediately.
Can be reheated at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together except eggs.
Add them last, one at a time and beat well.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Grate cheese and mix together.
Press into baking dish.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and flour.
Pour over cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve warm with crackers or chips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn in large bowl.
Make sure sugar is dissolved.
Add corn; pour into casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Cook for 45 to 50 minutes at 400°.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Shred cabbage.
Chop celery.
Brown hamburger meat with onion. Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Cook cabbage, celery and other vegetables until tender.
Pour hamburger and onion into the rest. Season to your taste.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Peel and boil until tender, then mash potatoes.
Add butter, sugar, salt and spices.
Make into balls around a marshmallow. Roll in crushed cornflakes and bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients well and drop into muffin pan. Bake at 400° until golden.

title: confetti appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mini bagels. Mix well and spread on mini bagel halves.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put in blender to combine.

title: allison's zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion and zucchini in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients together, except bread.
Stir the cubed bread with margarine; put on top.
Sprinkle with cheese on top of bread crumbs.
Bake until bubbly.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and 1/4 cup water.
Add 1 cup of chow mein noodles, dash of pepper and remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly. Turn into 10 x 6 x
1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining noodles on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon supreme dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Then fold in beaten egg whites.
In a 2-quart casserole, line bottom and sides with ladyfingers. Add lemon mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Can be made the day before, but wait until last minute to add Cool Whip.

title: greek style macaroni bake
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in next 2 ingredients and set aside.
Combine mayonnaise and flour; stir in milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add next 2 ingredients; stir in meat mixture.
In large pan, layer 1/2 cooked macaroni, then add 1/2 meat mixture.
Add remaining macaroni and meat.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes or until hot.

title: orange fluff
directions: Use no water and drain fruit well.
Sprinkle Jell-O over Cool Whip.
Add cottage cheese.
Fold in pineapple and oranges.
Chill.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Break bread into small pieces and moisten with milk.
Add bread to mixed ingredients.
Shape into cakes.
Fry quickly in vegetable oil until brown.
(Using enough oil to cover bottom of frying pan.)
Turn cakes once.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple, coconut and walnuts in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour cake mix on top then pour melted butter over that. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mary's christmas date roll candy
directions: Combine sugar, salt, milk and butter.
Simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Add dates.
Cook, stirring constantly, to soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat and cool to room temperature. Beat until creamy and thick.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour onto a cold, wet cloth.
Knead until smooth. Shape into a roll and wrap in wax paper.
Chill until firm.
Cut into thin slices.
This amount will cut about 30 slices.
Keep in a tightly covered box.

title: icicle pickles(14 day pickles)
directions: Cut cucumbers lengthwise. Dissolve pickling salt in 1 gallon boiling water and pour over cucumbers. Let stand 1 week, stirring each day. Drain off saltwater and cover cucumbers with clear boiling water. Let stand 24 hours. Drain off water. Dissolve alum in 1 gallon boiling water. Cover cucumbers with mixture and let stand 24 hours.

title: sally's cranberry coffee cake
directions: In large bowl, cream margarine and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Beat in almond extract.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beating well after each addition.
Spoon a third of batter into greased and floured Bundt or other 12-cup tube pan.
Crumble a third of cranberry sauce over batter.
Repeat layers two more times, ending with cranberry sauce.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Serve warm or cooled.
Drizzle glaze over top.
Serves about 20.

title: karen's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and margarine.
Add sugars, eggs, and vanilla.
Mix in flour, soda, baking powder, and salt.
Add oatmeal, walnuts, and coconut.
Drop on pan 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350 for 10-12 minutes.

title: cabbage-beef rolls
directions: Wash the cabbage; cut the stem end and core.
Put in a large kettle; cover with boiling salted water and cook until the leaves are loose enough to separate with a fork, about 20 minutes (more or less, depending upon size).
Remove the cabbage; drain and separate the leaves.
Or use one 15 1/2-ounce jar grape leaves.

title: crazy crunch for popcorn
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns to a light caramel color.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Pour over corn; coat well.
Store in tightly covered container. Can add salted nuts or peanuts.

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook over medium heat until it makes a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and hand beat until creamy.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown pork sausage, onion and green pepper and drain off fat. Add soup mix, water and wild rice and mix well in ovenproof bowl. Add almonds and mushrooms.
Bake covered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill overnight covered.
Cook juice, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar until slightly thickened.
Chill overnight.
In the morning, combine pineapple sauce with Cool Whip.
Fold in pineapple and marshmallow mixture. Add apples and nuts.

title: chocolate-butterscotch scotcheroos
directions: In large saucepan, cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Mix in cereal.
Press in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water the semi-sweet morsels and butterscotch flavored morsels, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Chill until firm (15 minutes).
Yields 48 (2 x 1-inch) bars.

title: chicken and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium heat.
Add chicken; cook and stir until browned.
Add broccoli, red pepper and water chestnuts; cook and stir until tender-crisp.
Mix broth, soy sauce, garlic powder and ginger; stir into chicken mixture.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Serve chicken and vegetables over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate and margarine over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, and salt.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Combine apricots, almonds, and coconut.
Stir half into the batter.
Pour into 9-inch greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining apricot mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 5 layer delight
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Let cool.

title: finnish pancakes
directions: Melt butter in a 12 x 16-inch pan.
Mix lightly with beater the milk and eggs, then add sugar, salt and flour.
Pour mixed batter over melted butter.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Serve with maple syrup.
Slice into squares.
Serves 10 to 15.
Good luck.

title: broiled shrimp and crab
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish; cook under broiler until butter is melted, stirring once.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pecan and coconut pie
directions: *Raisins
are
optional
but
if not used, increase the pecans and coconut to one cup each.

title: lib's chow chow
directions: Grind
tomatoes,
onions,
hot	peppers, sweet peppers, cabbages and cucumbers in food chopper.
Add salt and sugar to taste, about
cup each.
Let drain well; then squeeze out as much
liquid
as
possible	with
hands.
Bring apple cider vinegar, 7	1/2
cups sugar and pickling spice to a boil.
Add vegetable mixture
and
simmer
for
30 minutes.
Place in hot jars and seal.
Makes 13 pints.

title: spinach quiche(no crust)
directions: Line a pie plate with Jarlsberg cheese or Muenster cheese slices, overlapping just slightly and up to pie plate edge. Saute an onion in oil until transparent.
Add the drained spinach. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie plate and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: wine and wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice mix according to package directions on top of range.
Meanwhile, place onion, celery and butter in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Cook, covered in a countertop microwave oven until tender, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Blend in soup, sour cream, wine and curry.
Stir in chicken and cooked rice.
Microcook, covered, until heated through, 8 to 10 minutes, giving casserole a half turn after 5 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Beat together eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Fry ground sausage; drain.
Spread on crescent rolls.
Spread hash browns on sausage as desired. Sprinkle with grated cheese of choice.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, milk and cocoa and bring to a hard boil.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from stove and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Let set in bowl 1 or 2 minutes before dropping on foil.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Combine with all ingredients except peas.
Add peas last few minutes.
Cook about 1 1/2 to 2 hours on low heat.

title: connie's scotch shortbread
directions: Mix ingredients together with your fingers.
Press dough into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Prick with a fork.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and cut in squares while hot.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Warm milk in saucepan over low heat. Stir in rice. Bring to a simmer and cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, until the rice is tender, about 35 minutes. In a medium size bowl, whisk together the egg, sugar, vanilla and salt. Gradually stir in some of the rice mixture until well blended. Return the mixture to the saucepan and stir over low heat for 1 minute to cook the egg. Pour into bowl. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: quick tomato chili sauce(a shortcut)
directions: Combine vegetables and salt; let stand overnight. Drain well but do not press. Add other ingredients (spices tied in bag). Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or longer if wanted thicker. Put in pint jars and process 10 minutes. Makes 5 pints.

title: black bottom cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together the first 5 ingredients and blend.
Then add the next 3 ingredients.
Pour into skillet or pan and set aside.
Mix together the remaining 4 ingredients. Pour this mixture on top of first mixture.
Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.
Cool before serving.
When you spoon this cake into serving dishes, remember the bottom of the cake becomes the sauce topping.
Add whipped cream if desired.

title: greek shrimp pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions and drain. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat butter, garlic and wine over medium heat until butter is melted. Add shrimp, tomatoes and cilantro and saut the mixture over moderate high heat for 3 minutes or until shrimp are just firm to the touch but cooked through. Remove the skillet from heat. Stir in Feta cheese. Pour over linguine and sprinkle with Parmesan-Reggiano cheese if desired. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pierogi dough
directions: Melt butter in milk; be sure not to scald.
Mix eggs into flour.
Add sour cream and salt.
Keep adding milk and butter mixture until dough forms into a ball away from the bowl.
Roll out on floured surface and cut in circles.
Fill with favorite filling.
Pinch edges with fork and boil until they raise to surface of water.
Drain.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a large paper grocery bag (I double bag). Sprinkle onion soup mix over potatoes in bag and add oil.
Shake well.
Put potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been lightly sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes, stirring or turning every 15 minutes.
Serve with catsup or sour cream or Ranch dressing.

title: layered salad
directions: Use desired amounts for whatever size salad needed.
Do not mix ingredients, just layer one on top of other.
Start with lettuce; lay on bottom of bowl. Put down a layer of tomatoes. Layer on cheese, watercress, a layer of mayo, then layer bacon, avocados, then top with peas.
Put in a glass bowl, it's very decorative looking.
Very low calories.

title: rouladen
directions: Spread mustard on inside of steaks.
Add bacon and pickles (cut in strips).
Roll up and hold together with toothpick. Season with salt and pepper on outside.
Slightly saute onions in skillet, using margarine.
Add meat rolls; brown, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook for about 1 1/2 hours, until nice and brown, adding water if necessary.
Thicken drippings with flour. Add whipping cream, sugar, paprika and more salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with potato dumplings or spaetzle and almond carrots (buttered carrots with parsley and slivered almonds).
Serves 4.

title: chicken-rice oven dish
directions: Mix soups and rice; spread in large, flat pan or glass dish. Melt
butter.
Dip chicken in butter; lay on top of rice mixture. Dribble remaining butter on top.
Bake 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt, then shortening. Immediately add about 1/2 of the flour at one time.
Stir well, then gradually add rest of the flour.
When you can no longer stir, knead flour in until dough doesn't stick to fingers.
Knead a few minutes more and turn in greased bowl.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and make into rolls or loaves.
Turn rolls in melted greased pans.
Let rise again and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake a little longer for loaf.

title: posole (mexican soup)
directions: Heat oil and garlic in a 3-quart saucepan until oil is hot. Coat pork with flour.
Cook and stir pork in oil over medium heat until brown; remove pork with slotted spoon and drain.

title: nabisco torte
directions: Put Nabisco through chopper.
Press in form.
Keep a bit for the top.
Beat sugar and butter like cake; add 1 egg at a time. Cover Nabiscos with sugar and butter, then well drained pineapple, pecans, whipped cream and the rest of the crumbs.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Beat eggs.
Melt 1/4 stick margarine and add to eggs with salt, black pepper, garlic powder, Bisquick, Cheddar cheese and shredded zucchini.
Grease pan or 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: eagle brand milk pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar; beat to a cream.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour and alternate with milk.
Beat egg whites separately.
Fold into rest of mixture and pour into a 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine beef, milk, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and parsley. Brown beef and set aside.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and saute onion, mushrooms and paprika.
Sprinkle flour over mixture.
Add bouillon slowly.
Just before serving, pour in Worcestershire sauce and sour cream.
Great served over egg noodles.

title: barbara mandrell's pig picking cake
directions: Grease two 9-inch layer pans; line bottom with waxed paper and grease again and set aside.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using oil, eggs and juice drained from oranges.
Stir in oranges and nuts.
Spread evenly in prepared pans.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool pans on racks 10 minutes.
Remove cakes from pans; peel off wax paper and continue to cool on racks.
Place one layer on a serving plate and spread with 1/3 of the frosting.
Add second layer and frost top and sides of cake.
Makes 12 servings.

title: light bread
directions: Place sugar, shortening and salt in large bowl.
Add hot milk and stir to soften shortening.
Cool; beat in eggs.
Soften yeast in warm water.
Stir into shortening mixture.
Add 4 cups flour. Beat smooth. Add more flour, enough to make smooth, soft dough. Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Easy to prepare and delicious!

title: microwave beef and vegie casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper.
Place in a casserole dish forming a ring around a glass drinking glass in the middle.
Remove glass; arrange potatoes in center of ring.
Place carrots around outer edge.
Microwave covered, on Medium-high, for 25 minutes.
Rotate if your oven has hot spots.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix oil, applesauce and sugar in one bowl.
Blend all other ingredients in another bowl.
Mix together and pour into a tube or loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: sausage snack
directions: Fry sausage and onion, drain well.
Add cheese whiz and tomato paste.
Spread on party rye bread. Bake at 350° until edges brown and cheese bubbles.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Can make vanilla or chocolate.

title: grandma goodson's raw apple cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: green onion-cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth; gradually add milk, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in green onions.
Cover and chill up to 2 days.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Cream	butter and Crisco until fluffy.
Add sugar	and
beat
well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well
after
each.	Add
sour
cream, flour and baking powder.
Alternate with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Bake for 1	hour (check because it may need to bake 15 minutes longer).
This
cake
should
be
put in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Mix well and bake in a Pyrex dish (11 x 7-inch) at about 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Combine ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat on low speed until all ingredients are moistened.
Increase speed to medium and beat 1 minute.
Spoon batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove bread from pan and cool on a wire rack.

title: finnish chestnut fingers
directions: Cream butter or margarine and the 1/4 cup sugar thoroughly. Add egg yolk; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in chestnut puree and vanilla.
Stir flour, salt and cinnamon together thoroughly; stir into creamed mixture.
Roll into 2 1/2-inch long fingers, using a scant tablespoon dough for each finger.
Dip one side of each finger in slightly beaten egg white, then in sugar.
Place, sugar side up, on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 20 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet while hot.
Cool on wire rack.
Dip one end of each cookie in melted chocolate.
Place on waxed paper until chocolate hardens.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: salad
directions: Mix well.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: texas hot cocoa cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Heat oleo, cocoa, shortening and water until boils.
Pour into flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Makes thin batter.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and condensed milk thoroughly!
(Mix at least 15 minutes, the more the better.)
Add lime juice a little at a time and mix thoroughly, the more the better.
Pour into graham crust and chill for at least 24 hours.
The more the better.
The longer it is chilled, the better it slices.
Eat.
Keep what's left, if any, in the refrigerator.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, confectioners sugar and margarine together with fork until small beads form.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Soften cheese in microwave; add sour cream and blend with mixer until smooth.
Add onions.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, baking powder and sugar together. Using a fork, cut in shortening until it resembles cornmeal. Add cheese. Stir in buttermilk all at one time just until blended. Do not overstir. Drop by tablespoonfuls (I use an ice cream scoop to give biscuits a nicer shape) onto a well-greased baking sheet. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: turkey gravy
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Sprinkle herbs and flour over butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Add hot broth and stir briskly until thick and smooth.
Turn off heat and blend in cream.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
This can be stored in refrigerator.
Reheat gently.
Do not boil.
Yields 4 cups.

title: wacky cake
directions: In a 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan, sift together flour, sugar, salt, soda and cocoa.
Add vanilla, vinegar and salad oil.
Pour water over mixture and blend with fork.
Do not beat.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°. This cake is moist and low in cholesterol.

title: sour cream rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Mix granulated sugar, chopped nuts, melted butter and cinnamon and set aside for topping.

title: archduke ferdinand's pot roast
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown meat on both sides in hot oil; drain off fat.
Stir together the soup, wine, garlic, bay leaf, allspice, salt and pepper; pour over meat.
Add celery and carrot. Cover; simmer for 1/2 to 2 hours, or until meat is tender. Remove meat and vegetables to platter; keep warm.
Combine 2 tablespoons cold water and cornstarch; stir into sauce in Dutch oven.
Cook and stir until bubbly; cook and stir 2 minutes more. Spoon some sauce over meat.
Pass remainder.
Serves 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions 5 minutes. Mix soup and sour cream, fold in squash and onions.
Combine stuffing and butter.
Spread half in baking dish.
Spoon vegetables on top.
Sprinkle stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crunchy apple crisp
directions: Place pie filling
in 8 x 10-inch buttered baking dish. Combine flour, oats,
sugar,
salt
and spices.
Stir in nuts. Add butter and mix
well.
Spread on top of apple pie filling. Bake at 375°
for
30 minutes.
Serve warm topped with whipped cream.

title: sword in the bag
directions: Shake the flour around in a microwave cooking bag or Ziploc bag.
Add fish.
Add tomatoes, onion, basil, thyme and garlic. Tie a knot in the top of the bag (or "zip" the bag) and poke 6 ot 7 slits in the bag.

title: bean and frito salad
directions: Combine beans and onions.
Marinate in French dressing a few hours or overnight.
Add lettuce broken into bite size pieces, grated cheese and corn chips broken into small pieces.
Toss and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place hamburger in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cheese on top, then the onion slices.
Mix soups with a little milk, then pour over top.
Cover with Tater Tots and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: old fashion prune cake
directions: Cream oleo and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and prunes.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and spices; sift together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add oats and mix thoroughly.
Bake in 2 oiled 9-inch cake pans at 375° for 25 minutes or oiled Bundt pan for 40 to 45 minutes.
Pour icing over after punching holes with ice pick.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Mix brownie mix as directed on package.
Place on a greased pizza pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes until done.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in well drained pineapple. Spread over brownie crust.
Top with fruit and nuts.
Melt chocolate and butter, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over pizza. Chill.

title: spinach-potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Easy to double.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Stir Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk up. Stir well, then add ReaLemon juice. Mix well and pour into a graham cracker or vanilla cookie crust. Chill.

title: swedish cakes
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream until light.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add.
Blend in flour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Finely chop nuts.
Dip balls into egg white (unbeaten), then nuts.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and press fairly flat with a glass.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and press center down; bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool and fill with jam. Makes 15 to 18 cookies.

title: cocktail reubens
directions: Combine kraut, cheese and meat.
Add mayonnaise to hold together.
Spread on cocktail rye bread.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes until cheese bubbles.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 9-inch pan or 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: poor man's turkey and dressing
directions: Prepare Stove Top according to package.
Take 2 tablespoonfuls of stuffing.
Put on a slice of turkey and roll up. Place into an ovenproof baking dish and repeat with remaining stuffing and turkey.
When all the turkey and stuffing have been put into the pan, pour gravy over the top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 35 minutes.

title: nanny's cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage in half.
Slice as thin as possible to get long strips.
Put in a bowl.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Alternate layers of chicken, noodles and stuffing.
Place the chicken in a large casserole dish.
Put sauce (a combination of soups plus the leftover broth from the cooked noodles).
Manage to have enough sauce to cover each layer.
When all is used, sprinkle grated cheese over the top of the dish.
Put in the oven and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
"Very good and tasty!
A big casserole!"

title: skillet chicken teriyaki
directions: Mix soy sauce, water, sugar, garlic and ginger together. Saute chicken in oil, about 10 minutes.
Remove chicken; drain oil.
Return chicken to pan; pour sauce over the pieces.
Bring to a boil, then cover.
Simmer for 20 minutes, turning occasionally. Serve with sauce over rice.

title: strawberry bundt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Combine cake and pudding mix.
Add the eggs, oil, juice, Galliano and vodka.
Beat on low speed for 1/2 minute.
Beat on medium speed for 5 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove to rack and pour on glaze while cake is still warm.

title: homesteaders' rabbit or squirrel with cream gravy
directions: In large plastic food storage bag, combine flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Shake to mix.
Add rabbit pieces; shake to coat. Reserve excess flour mixture.

title: cholesterol-free banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mix first 7 ingredients.
With pastry blender, cut in corn oil spread until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in bananas, apple juice, egg substitute, walnuts and vanilla just until flour is moistened. Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 60 minutes.
Cool bread on rack. Remove from pan.
Makes 18 servings.
Diabetics can indulge.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all together in a large mouth gallon jar and fill with thinly sliced cucumbers and 2 sliced onions.

title: margarita slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 5-quart ice cream pail.
Freeze. Serve in tall glass mixed with 7-up or sour.

title: mexicalli pie
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in hot oil until tender.
Stir in chili powder, cumin, garlic powder and salt.
Cook 1 minute more. Cool.
Stir in beans, rice, cheese, eggs and milk.
Spray a 10-inch microwave-safe pie plate with nonstick cooking spray coating.
Add rice mixture.
Microcook, uncovered, on 50% power (Medium), 22 to 24 minutes or until center is set, giving dish a quarter turn twice during cooking.

title: lemon pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Add egg yolks to condensed milk and stir well. Add lemon juice to taste.
Pour in pie shell.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Line pan with bacon strips.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes one large skillet.

title: dad's armadillo eggs
directions: Slit peppers lengthwise and remove seeds.
Leave stem on. Combine other ingredients in food processor and then stuff peppers with this mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Serve with Ranch dressing to dip in.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except the package of ham.
Spread mixture on each slice of ham and roll jelly roll style.
Wrap and refrigerate until well chilled; slice into slices and serve with crackers.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with Pam. In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat flour, margarine, sugar and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press firmly into prepared pan and bake for 20 to 23 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mom's salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: creamy fruit salad dressing
directions: Blend fruit juice and sour cream into mayonnaise in a small bowl.
Mix in nuts.
Chill until serving time.
Serve over fruit salad.
Vary amount of fruit juice for desired consistency.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve over lettuce leaves as a salad or make sandwiches.
Great on raisin bread.

title: pan rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water in large bowl.
Add dry milk, sugar, salt, melted shortening and 3 cups flour.

Blend at low speed until moistened, then beat for 3 minutes at medium speed. Using a spoon, stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough. Turn dough on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Divide dough into 24 pieces; shape into balls.
Place in 2 greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Cover; let rise until doubled (about 30 minutes).
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pepperoni 'n cheese crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut cheese into triangles.
On ungreased cookie sheet, separate rolls into triangles.
Place 3 slices of pepperoni and one slice of cheese on each roll.
Start at shortest side of triangle and roll to opposite point; curve into crescent shape.
Brush roll with egg white.
Bake 10 to 14 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt thoroughly and let stand 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix together sugar and vinegar. Combine all ingredients.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Place in freezer container and freeze immediately.

title: low calorie gravy
directions: Add enough water to broth to make 2 cups.
Gradually stir into cornstarch in small bowl until smooth.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips together.

title: easy beef tips in mushroom sauce
directions: Put meat in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour mushroom soup, undiluted, over meat.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Pour soda over all.
Do not season!!
Bake at 275° for four hours.
Do not open oven door!
Let stand 30 minutes before serving.
Delicious! Serve over rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Chill beans.
When cold, pour beans into a bowl and rinse with water until sauce is gone.
Drain.
Pour into large bowl the chopped onions, lettuce and tomatoes.
Pour in with the beans. Add grated cheese.
Pour dressing over salad; mix well. Refrigerate for a couple of hours.
When ready to serve, crush the bag of corn chips and stir in the salad.

title: francis marion hotel poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend first five ingredients.
Slowly add oil.
Stir in poppy seed.
This dressing is very good over green spinach salad, tossed green lettuce or fruit salad.

title: cheese dip for nachos
directions: Cut Velveeta and Colby cheese into cubes; melt in crock-pot. Chop medium onion.
Brown ground chuck in frying pan; add medium onion.
Mix taco seasoning to ground chuck and simmer.
Add ground chuck mixture to melted cheese, then add refried beans.
You may need to add a little milk to make creamy.
Leave crock-pot on low to keep warm and serve with nacho chips.
Enjoy!

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pork chops in large baking dish and sprinkle with salt.
Top each pork chop with onion slice and lemon slice.
Mix brown sugar and catsup in small bowl and pour over pork chops.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
Mix eggs, cottage and Ricotta cheese and seasoning.
Set aside.
Cook mushrooms, onions and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper, then add milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in spinach or broccoli, carrots and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 of noodles.
Spread 1/3 of cheese mixture over, then 1/3 of vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat these steps 2 more times.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, covered.
This can also be made ahead of time and placed in the freezer until needed.

title: coconut candy
directions: Melt the oleo in saucepan. Remove from heat. Add powdered sugar and coconut.
Mix well.
Shape rounded teaspoonful of mixture into balls.
Make indent in center of each and place on cookie sheet. Fill centers with melted chocolate.
Chill until firm. Store in refrigerator.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: mexi chili chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Wash and dry chicken. Coat with mayonnaise.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Put chicken in shallow baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: layer lemon lush
directions: Mix together like pie crust. Spread or pat in 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or more until brown. Cool.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and nuts.
Put into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Put remaining Cool Whip on top of this and sprinkle with a few nuts.

title: icebox cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
These will keep in refrigerator for 1 year.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking 45 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Put sweet potatoes in baking dish.
Add sugars, butter and milk.
Turn oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: white bread plus
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water; add sugar and blend.
Let stand in a warm place for 40 minutes.
Beat in egg, shortening, salt, sugar and 2 cups of the water.
Stir in some of the flour to form a thick batter, then pour onto floured board and knead in remaining flour, about 10 minutes.
Place in a well-greased bowl and let stand until double in size.
Knead in edges.
Turn dough and let stand in warm place until double in size.
Cut into three equal portions and shape into loaves.
Place in well-greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans and let rise until double in bulk.
Place in cold oven, turn heat to 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce to 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven, brush with melted shortening and turn onto wire rack to cool.

title: easy frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat with electric mixer until smooth and spreadable.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Combine water and milk; set aside. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar.
No cooking.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion and celery in margarine.
Add mushroom soup, water, Cheez Whiz, rice and broccoli.
Mix all together. Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; save broth.
Debone chicken.
Melt margarine and pour over crumbs.
Put layer of dressing, then layer of chicken.
Pour 2 cups chicken broth over casserole, then pour over it the chicken and mushroom soups.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef with the green pepper and onion. To this, add both soups and oregano.
Make layers of ingredients as follows:
noodles, meat mixture, mushrooms, pepperoni and cheese, ending with cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: homemade fried rice
directions: Boil rice according to instructions on box.
Use less water for flaky rice.
Boil or cook meat or shrimp until done.
Add a little salt and pepper.
When meat is done, dice into small pieces.
Scramble eggs; add green peppers, onions, celery and bean sprouts.
Cook together until vegetables are soft.
Cook in butter or oil.
Add rice.
Stir for about 10 minutes.
Add soy sauce, salt and pepper.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add flour and mix well.
Dough will be very soft.
Do not let dough rise.
Store dough in a covered airtight container in refrigerator.
Use as needed for warm yeast rolls by filling muffin pan cups (sprayed with Pam baking spray) 1/2 full of dough.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes. Serve warm.

title: potato and broccoli soup
directions: Mix all in a saucepan and add milk as needed to thin to soup consistency.
Bring to a boil but do not boil.
Sprinkle top with grated Parmesan cheese and bacon bits if desired.

title: mandarin orange szechuan stir-fry
directions: Mix soy sauce, water, honey, chili paste, pepper and cornstarch in bowl.
Over high heat, brown meat quickly.
Saute vegetables, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes with garlic.
Add orange zest.
Saute 1 more minute.
Add liquid mixture.
Let boil 30 seconds.
Serve over rice.

title: eight layer dip
directions: Mix package of taco seasoning with 1 of the packages of sour cream.
Set aside.
Mash the avocados and add the remaining sour cream; set aside.
Shred the cheese and set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer refried beans, picante sauce, taco seasoning/sour cream, avocados/sour cream, tomatoes, onion, black olives and shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: t.j. miracle soup(for the dieters)
directions: Cut vegetables and cover with water in a large pot.
Add dry onion soup mix, pepper and garlic, if desired (no salt).
Boil 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onions in oleo; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add sour cream after flour mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add water chestnuts.
Layer green beans in casserole dish and add sour cream mixture.
Top with cheese and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Place meat in crock-pot.
Cover with sliced onion.
Combine garlic, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, salt, paprika and mustard.
Stir in water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low for 9 to 10 hours.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Dice and boil potatoes until tender.
While potatoes are cooking, add onion (salt and pepper added to second cooking). After potatoes are tender, drain water and whip potatoes with mixer.
Add milk; stir over burner until potato soup thickens.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
(Reserve 1/3 cup sugar to beat with egg whites.)
Add flavoring.
Blend egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

Sift flour, soda and salt together and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Fold in egg whites beaten to soft peaks with the reserved sugar. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a Bundt pan or tube pan (or you can use several loaf pans).
Cool 30 minutes in pan before turning out.
This cake is better about four days old and can be stored in the freezer for several weeks.

title: crock-pot navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans for 12 hours and drain.
Place all ingredients in a 2-quart crock-pot or slow cooker.
Cook for 15 hours on low setting.
Remove ham hock and discard skin, fat and bone.
Cut meat in small pieces and place in soup.
Beans can be mashed if desired.

title: super fast franks and beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix beans in spaghetti sauce, onion and cheese in an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Place franks on top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until beans are bubbling and franks have a touch of brown.
Sprinkle with cheese and cook 5 minutes more, until cheese melts.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter; while melting in another container, mix sugar, cocoa and flour, then pour into melted butter and mix well.
Add 1 egg at a time, mixing well after each one, until you have added all 3 eggs.
Add vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp fettuccine
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Cook green onions and garlic in a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium heat, stirring constantly 1 minute.
Add shrimp; cook, stirring constantly until shrimp turns pink.
Stir in parsley and Alfredo Sauce; add fettuccine.
Toss gently.
Serve immediately. Yield:
6 servings.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Combine pretzels, 1 tablespoon sugar and margarine.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 400°.
Set aside to cool.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 25 individual rolls.
Pour sauce over meat rolls.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Combine bread cubes and 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into greased 2-quart dish.
