Melt butter; brown remaining crumbs and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add one egg at a time; mixing well. Crush wafers and add alternately with 1/2 cup milk, coconut and nuts.
Bake at 275 degrees for 45 minutes; increase oven temperature to 350 degrees and bake another 45 minutes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Roll chicken in bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano and garlic.
Melt butter and brown chicken.
Remove chicken into baking dish.
Add scallions, carrots and white wine to frypan; cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour butter and wine mix over chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.
Can make ahead.

title: nadine's molasses (stack) cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs; add molasses. Sift flour, spices and salt together.
Add to mixture.
Put soda in boiling water and add to batter, beating constantly by hand. Pour into 4 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and stack together with applesauce between the layers.

title: pistachio dream salad
directions: Layer 1:
Mix 1 cup flour with 1/8 cup powdered sugar, 1/2 cup melted butter and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan (little Pam).
Bake 20 minutes (until it browns just a little).

title: orange julius drink
directions: Put all in blender and blend on high until ice is crushed and drink is fluffy. DO NOT try to double the recipe; it won't taste the same.

title: sweet irish bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour angel cake pan. Set aside.

title: chicken in red bell peppers(low-fat, big taste!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Tear off a big old piece of Saran Wrap and lay the fillets on top of it, leaving enough

room to put the remaining wrap on top of the fillets to cover and allowing room for flattening in next step. Pound the fillets with a kitchen mallet or your fist until they are fairly flat. Remove the top layer of Saran Wrap and sprinkle the tarragon over the chicken as well as either the garlic salt or thin slivers of garlic. Salt and pepper to taste. Core the red bell peppers and wash them out so that there are no seeds or whitish pulp inside. Roll up the fillets (like cigars) and stuff each one into a red pepper. Pour just a little olive oil into each red bell pepper and place them in a glass baking dish, lying flat. Pour 1/2 cup white wine and 1/2 cup chicken stock into the baking dish, along with a clove of fresh garlic that has been sliced or pressed. Cover dish with aluminum foil and bake for 25 minutes. Remove foil and cook for another 25 minutes.

title: holiday tuna tree recipe
directions: Makes 4 cups.
In a large bowl, combine cream cheese and tuna. Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Place in Christmas tree mold and refrigerate.
You may serve in the mold or transfer to a serving plate.
Decorate with garlands of small parsley leaves, red and green peppers cut into stars and a lemon wedge.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add corn syrup and salt; beat well. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add pecans and vanilla and stir. Pour into a pastry lined 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for about an hour until golden brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: fruit salad delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Fold in Cool Whip, nuts and coconut.
Delicious over pound cake.

title: fish and rice roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in small pan with salt, pepper and lemon juice. Add 1/2 cup of broccoli.
Place rice in a bowl and pour 3/4 of mixture over rice.
Mix.
Lay fish out flat.
Spoon rice mixture onto fish and roll each piece of fish up.
Fasten with a toothpick to keep fish in a roll.
Place rolls in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Pour the rest of the rice mixture over the fish.
Place one slice of lemon on each fish roll.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: jane's sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers 24 hours in lime mixed with water to cover. Rinse and soak in clear water for 2 hours.
Drain and add vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours; pack in jars and seal.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon, in a quart casserole. Mix well.
Place bacon pieces on top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick mix according to package directions.
Add sausage and cheese.
Mix well and shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: lizzie's carrot cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients and set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, carrots and pecans until well blended.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix at a low speed until sugar dissolves (approximately 2 minutes).
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of the pan.

title: english trifle
directions: This recipe will make 4 servings using 1 box of custard mix; may be doubled.

title: candy yams
directions: Boil and peel apples and yams.
Slice.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Layer apples and yams in baking dish.
Pour sauce over them.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: In a large pot, brown hamburg.
Add vegetables and let simmer. Stir occasionally. Beat egg and milk. Add to mixture. Add raisins. Prepare bread stuffing according to package directions and add to mixture. Remove from heat and cool.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring and chocolate to make a paste.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix.
Add paste mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add
buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix real good.
Bake 350 degrees 25 - 30 minutes or until done.
Use three 8 inch pans.

title: oriental pork chops
directions: In medium hot skillet, mix water and soy sauce.
Layer pork chops and top with green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle ginger.
Cook on medium heat until pork chops are done.
Remove chops and add rice to remaining skillet ingredients.
If there is not enough liquid, add more water and soy to desired taste.
Add pork chops and warm.
Serves 8.

title: steak fajitas
directions: Marinate steak in oil, juice and garlic overnight.
Saute meat until brown.
Add green peppers and onion until partially soft. Remove from heat.
Serve immediately.
Have each person serve themselves a spoonful of meat mixture in tortilla, then top with sour cream, tomato, lettuce and cheese.
Fold and eat.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put butter and water in 2-quart saucepan on high.
When mixture boils, add flour; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
When mixture gathers into a mass, remove from heat.
Place mixture in a bowl of electric mixer.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Place in mounds on greased cookie sheet about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake in preheated electric oven at 400° for 40 minutes, or with an oven meal at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: gooey cherry butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix and 2 eggs; pour on top of butter.
On top of this, pour cherry pie filling.
Combine cream cheese (softened), 2 eggs and powdered sugar in that order.
Spread over cherry mixture.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, bean dip and sour cream.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Brown ground beef and add taco mix and water according to package directions.
Place mixture on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Add chopped tomatoes and chopped onion. Place grated cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho cheese Doritos.

title: fresh blueberry pie iii
directions: Place 2 cups of fresh blueberries in baked pie shell. In a saucepan, combine water, cornstarch, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 3/4 cup sugar. Mix well and add 2 cups fresh or frozen blueberries. Bring to a boil and continue to boil for 5 minutes or until thick and clear. Add butter and lemon juice. Pour filling over berries in pie shell and allow to cool. Makes 1 pie (8 servings).

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add baking powder and milk.
Melt margarine in casserole.
Pour in batter.
Place fruit and juice on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: delicious hush puppies
directions: Mix above ingredients except beer.
Add beer to dry mixture until desired consistency.
Mixture should be thick enough to remain on spoon to drop into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown. Drain and serve.

title: fresh tongue
directions: Wash tongue.
Place in pot. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil. Simmer over low heat until tender, allowing about 50 minutes per pound.
Let tongue cool in cooking liquid. Remove skin. Slice and serve cold or hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Bring to a boil the soup, water and tomatoes.
Cook onion with hamburger.
Put a layer of Doritos (slightly crushed) into bottom of casserole dish.
Put a layer of hamburger, then soup, then Doritos, etc., until all ingredients are used.
Top with cheese. Heat in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put
in 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake
at 350° for 30
minutes.
Sprinkle
cup Mozzarella cheese and heat until cheese melts.

title: nachos
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Spread chips on 2 cooking sheets.
Spread ground beef on top of chips.
Pour 1/2 jar of salsa per pan on meat (soaks into meat).
Spread 1/2 Cheddar cheese on meat per pan.
Spread 1/2 Mozzarella cheese per pan.
Heat oven to 350° and cook for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken, salt and pepper, in a large baking dish (at least 3-quart).
Skin chicken and remove fat. Place chicken pieces on top and add salt and pepper to chicken. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: beef ole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add tomato paste and two cans of water. Add both packages of the seasonings and tomatoes. Simmer until hot. Serve this over Fritos and add lettuce, tomatoes, shredded cheese, onions, sour cream and black olives on top.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Use 1/3 cup mix per cup of water.
(Heat water first, then add mix, if using microwave.)

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, lay the portions of boneless chicken breasts.
Pour uncooked rice.
Cover and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
If the rice is dry, add water to it, about half way through.

title: fast "n" fabulous fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 9-inch tube pan and line with waxed paper.
Grease again (or use generously greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan).
Sift together flour and baking soda; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, mincemeat, sweetened condensed milk, fruit and nuts.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.

title: fig preserves
directions: Soak figs in soda water for 1 hour.
Drain and rinse well. Place figs in large shallow roasting pan and sprinkle sugar over all.
Pour in 2 to 3 cups water, enough water so the bottom of the pan is covered.
Add lemon slices and cinnamon sticks.
Bring to boil; turn down fire so that there is always bubbling to top.
Do not stir very often.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until figs are easily pierced with a straw.
Take off scum.
Fill sterilized jars.
Make sure 2 slices of lemon and 1 cinnamon stick are in each jar.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add sweet potatoes, vanilla and melted butter.
Mix together, then add milk. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels. Add the milk.
Mix and add pecans.
Drop by teaspoons on buttered cookie sheet and freeze for 1 hour.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles until almost done.
Mix remaining ingredients, except potato chips, which you sprinkle on the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatine in 4 tablespoons cold water.
Add 1 cup boiling water; dissolve sugar into water.
Add pineapple with juice and the juice of 1 lemon.
Put mixture into the refrigerator and let jell slightly.

title: chicken with mushroom peppercorn sauce
directions: Remove skin from chicken; rinse and pat dry.
Spray a cold, large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Cook chicken in hot skillet about 10 minutes, turning to brown evenly.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Lightly crush cornflakes; reserve 1/4 cup margarine.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Mix crushed cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Pour over other mixture. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Do not cover.

title: zesty fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruits and the juices except mandarin orange juice. Add dry pudding.
Chill.
Makes a creamy fruit salad.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Layer undrained pineapple, blueberries, sugar and cake mix in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Do not stir.
Drizzle with butter; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grinder sandwiches
directions: Saute in olive oil, green pepper, onion, garlic. Place shaved ham and mozzarella on buns. Pour saute mixture on top of cheese. Sprinkle with oregano or seasoning. Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 30 min. Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: country fried round steak dinner
directions: Fry steak on both sides until brown.
Remove from skillet. Place in roaster.
After removing steak from skillet, make a full skillet of gravy with flour and milk.
Peel potatoes and onions and place on top of steak in roaster.
Pour gravy over all.
Bake in slow oven until vegetables are done and meat is tender.

title: 3 bean soup
directions: Combine beans with remaining ingredients (except chicken) in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add chicken or ham pieces or both and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until meat is cooked and tender.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 quarts.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Add slowly flour, milk, cocoa and baking powder.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss broccoli, peanuts, raisins and green onions.

title: green rice
directions: Cook onion, celery and green pepper in margarine until tender. Add Cheez Whiz and soup, cook until cheese is melted and all ingredients are mixed well.
Add rice and broccoli.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° until done (30 minutes).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers.
(I use a blender.)
Place in a large pot with vinegar, sugar and food coloring.
Mix thoroughly.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; skim and add Certo. Pour into jars.
Makes approximately 6 pints.

title: the ultimate butterscotch chocolate chip recipe
directions: Mix the first four ingredients.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to margarine mixture.
Mix in butterscotch chips and nuts.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch square pan; mix flour, sugar and baking powder with milk.
Pour batter over the melted butter and add 2 cups of sweetened fruit, either canned or frozen, to mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Rinse chicken and place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix together soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Smooth over with spoon to cover chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in oven at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: great party dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Combine hamburger and salsa.
Simmer for one hour.
Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Serve with taco chips.

title: italian chicken delight
directions: Dip chicken in beaten egg, coating well, then roll in bread crumbs. Brown in oil. Drain chicken and place in casserole dish in a single layer. To oil left in skillet, add tomato sauce, salt, pepper, garlic powder, butter and basil. Simmer and pour over chicken in casserole. Seal with aluminum foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Uncover and top with grated Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese; return to oven for 10 minutes longer. Serves 4 to 6.

title: black forest cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 can pie filling, oil and eggs.
Beat well with mixer until batter is smooth (it will be very thick).
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool in pan 15 to 20 minutes.
Invert onto rack to finish cooling. Decorate with remaining can of pie filling, Hershey's syrup and Cool Whip.

title: meat loaf no. 3
directions: Mix ground beef, buttermilk, onion, salt and pepper and bread well and put in baking dish.
In a bowl mix together pickle juice, ketchup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour this mixture over the meat and bake on 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add sugar gradually and beat.
Add chocolate chips, nuts and flavoring.
(Can use small amounts of coloring.) Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Turn oven off; place pan in oven and let stand overnight.
Do not open oven.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use tube pan.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Put a layer of coconut in 9 x 13-inch pan greased pan. Sprinkle chopped nuts over coconut.
Add German chocolate cake mix (mix as directed on box) and pour over coconut and chopped
nuts. Then mix melted butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Put this on top of cake and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: grandma's gingerbread
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg and stir in melted shortening, molasses and hot water.
Bake in greased and lightly floured 9-inch square pan in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Can add raisins.
Serve warm.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger and onion in oil until done.
Remove from pan. Add to other ingredients.
Put in baking dish; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Bring to a boil in a saucepan water, margarine and molasses.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook garlic in the margarine over a medium heat, about 3 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add spinach and tomatoes. Simmer another 15 minutes.
Serve topped with grated cheese.

title: eastern style barbecue pork
directions: Combine everything but the meat in a saucepan and heat until boiling.
In a baking pan, place the pork.
Add a little sauce on top and cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 2 hours or as many hours as it takes your pork to be done.
Finely chop the pork and add a little more sauce.
This recipe is great with the Barbecue Slaw and Baked Beans.

title: doctors pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and eggs.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in Bundt pan.

title: banana split dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, sour cream, 1/4 cup lemon juice and vanilla and mix well.
Chill.

title: white chocolate pie
directions: Whip the cream until stiff and mix all ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: noodle kugel(noodle pudding)
directions: Cream the eggs and sugar either with an electric mixer or rotary beater.
Add noodles, sugar, raisins, lemon juice and rind, seasonings and butter.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle toasted bread crumbs over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 1 hour or until browned.
May be served with any meat dish.

title: magic fruit cake
directions: Chop all fruit into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients and press down into any kind of pan that has been greased. Bake at 300° approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour. Remove from pan just as soon as you take out of the oven.

title: sugarless banana walnut cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan.
In a bowl beat bananas and butter until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, powder, soda, and cinnamon and add to banana mixture, alternating with water and beating well after each addition.
Stir in the nuts. Spoon into pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Yields 9 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In large bowl, combine oil, eggs, vanilla and sugar; mix well. In separate bowl, sift flour and cinnamon. Add to egg mixture; mix well. Stir in apples, nuts and chips. Pour in metal 9 x 13 pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: no bake date balls
directions: Melt butter or margarine over low heat.
Add dates and beaten eggs.
Add sugar and cook for 12 to 15 minutes over low heat.
Add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Let cool until you can handle the dough.
Form small balls and roll in coconut.
Let cool.

title: pastry crust
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour and salt; cut in shortening until crumbly. Sprinkle with water, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing until dough is just moist enough to hold together. Form into a ball.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups sugar over cut up strawberries; let dissolve, then boil for 5 minutes.
Take off the eye and add 1 1/2 cups more sugar.
Dissolve and boil for 15 minutes.
Skim off the foam.
Pour into crock for 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Then ladle into hot sterilized jars and cover with paraffin.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients (except chicken) in saucepan.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Baste chicken often on grill; keep it very moist.
Grill 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Double recipe for a lot of chicken.

title: russian cream fruit mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Chill until partially congealed.
Fold in pineapple, peaches, coconut and sour cream. Turn into 5 cup salad mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with peach slices and coconut snowballs.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let set at room temperature for at least 1 hour.
Mix together and roll in chili powder.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato paste.
Put in dish.
Top with tomato paste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: oven donuts
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and then add egg and mix.
Sift dry ingredients and add milk.
Fill buttered muffin tins half full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan and roll in butter and 1/2 cup sugar mixed with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: chocolate chipper chews
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy; blend in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add and combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well; stir in candies.
Drop dough by tablespoons onto a greased cookie sheet about 3 inches apart.
Press 3 to 4 additional candies into cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on cookie sheet about 3 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar, vinegar and salt, then pour over the salad mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Grease only the bottom of 2 9 X 5 inch loaf pans.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine all dry ingredients, mix well.
In medium bowl, mix oil, water, eggs, and pumpkin.
Add flour mixture, beat for 1 minute at medium speed.
Fold in pecans.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool on wire racks.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and onion on a large piece of heavy-duty foil. Dot with margarine.
Combine cheese, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Fold foil over potatoes and add broth.
Seal the edges well.
Grill, covered, on medium heat for 35 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: flakey biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
(I use self-rising flour, as it has all the three dry ingredients.)
Cut in shortening in dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast with sugar and warm water.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk to dry ingredients. Mix lightly with fork.
Do not knead.
Refrigerate at least overnight in airtight container.
(The green Tupperware lettuce bowl is a good size for this.)
Pinch off amount needed.
Knead good.
Roll out and cut.
Bake about 10 minutes at 450°.
Do not allow biscuits to rise before baking.
The longer they sit in refrigerator, the better they are.
This recipe is especially good when you have company coming and can get biscuits made up several days ahead.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Add chicken and cook until done.
Next, add chicken broth, green beans, salt, basil and pepper. Bring this mixture to a boil and then add rice.
Cook 2 minutes covered; then turn off heat.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: barbecue beef or pork
directions: Put all in pan and bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 45 minutes.

title: reuben meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine the egg, onion, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper. Stir in rice. Crumble beef over the mixture and mix well. Shape into 15 balls. Place in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 15-20 minutes or until browned; drain. Arrange sauerkraut over meatballs; sprinkle with caraway seeds. Combine soup and salad dressing; spread over the top. Cover and bake for 35-45 minutes or until meat is no longer pink. Uncover; sprinkle
with Swiss cheese, place back in oven until cheese is melted. Serve with rye bread, if desired.

title: *pecan chews
directions: Mix in the order given.
Spread in an ungreased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake in a slow 260° oven for 1 hour.
Cut into squares or bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: coconut macaroon delight
directions: Grease 8-inch round baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Put macaroons in dish.
In bowl, mix all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over macaroons.
Place pan in water bath (larger pan filled 1/2 with water; place macaroon pan inside).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and water bath and cool.
Serve with whipped topping and garnish (nuts, cherries, etc.).

title: butterscotch nut cake
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, butter and 1/4 cup milk in saucepan and cook until small amount forms hard ball in cold water.
Stir constantly after mixture starts to boil.
Remove from fire and stir in 1 1/4 cups hot milk gradually; cool.
Blend shortening, salt and vanilla.
Add 3/4 cup sugar gradually and cream well. Add eggs singly and beat well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder 3 times.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with butterscotch mixture, mixing each addition until smooth.
Pour in 2 square 8-inch greased pans.
Sprinkle nuts over batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: buttery fish
directions: Place butter and onion in 9 x 13-inch baking dish in 350° oven until butter is melted.
Combine cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, salt, oregano and garlic.
Dip fish fillets in the butter then in crumb mixture.
Arrange fillets in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fish is tender.
In summer, wrap individually in foil and cook on grill until fish flakes.

title: deep dish pumpkin pie
directions: In hot oil, fry quickly a flour tortilla, turning to brown both sides.
Dust with cinnamon sugar.

title: cake mix cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix and knead first 4 ingredients.
Place in greased pan until doubled in bulk.
Roll out about 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with softened butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Put in pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar, butter and water mix. Best to divide dough in half to work with it.
I like to put some extra sugar and butter in pan before I put in rolls.

title: beets with tomato and onion - indian style
directions: Heat the oil in a saucepan.
Add the cumin, garlic and onion and cook until the onions are soft.
Add the flour and cayenne and cook for a minute more.

Add the beets, tomatoes, salt and water and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until beets are cooked. Uncover and cook for 7 minutes to thicken the sauce. I took these to a potluck once and after most of the guests had gone, the host was seen polishing off the leftovers straight from the pot.

title: chicken jambalaya(serves 4)
directions: In a large skillet, cook celery, onion and green pepper in margarine or butter until vegetables are tender.
Stir in the undrained tomatoes, chicken broth, rice, basil or thyme, garlic salt, pepper, hot pepper sauce and bay leaf.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in chicken.
Cook until heated through.
Discard bay leaf.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix
shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon extract and beat for
minutes
in mixer.
Add flour, soda and salt. Add buttermilk, beat
minutes
more.
Bake
in
greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut in bite size pieces.
In casserole dish melt 1 stick oleo.
Spread chicken over butter.
Add mixed vegetables and 1 can cream of chicken soup to which has been added the chicken broth.
Mix flour and milk and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until crust rises to top and browns.

title: lazy girl cake
directions: Use any type of fruit (I prefer apples) and prepare as for a pie.
In long baking dish, put apple filling in, then take 1 box yellow cake mix and sprinkle over apples.
Slice 1 stick margarine over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Real good with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: rice pudding
directions: Spread rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar or more if you like it sweeter.
Sprinkle nutmeg over this and add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Stir in 1/2 cup raisins.
Mix up 3 eggs with 2 cups whole milk or diluted canned milk.
Pour this mixture over rice and stir.
Set in pan of water to bake at 350° to 400° for about an hour.

title: soft butter
directions: Beat margarine until soft. Gradually add oil and buttermilk. Makes 2 pints of soft butter.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Combine the 1/4 cup Bisquick, brown sugar, salt, vinegar and water in a saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter; cool.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook the pasta and drain well.
In a casserole dish, place a small amount of sauce on the bottom.
Add 1/2 the pasta.
Cover with sauce, then layer green pepper, onion and pepperoni.
Top with cheese.
Repeat 1 more layer, then bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken breast in buttered casserole dish, top with 1/2 of the Ritz crackers. Mix soups and sour cream together, pour over chicken. Top with remaining crackers. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, add oil and sugar, blending well.
Add eggs.
Blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamy mixture.
Mix well.
Add apples, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or, if using tube pan, bake for 1 hour.
May also bake in 2 or 3 layers.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to directions on the box.
Add cream cheese and mix together.
Melt margarine.
Blend margarine and graham cracker crumbs together.
Put half of crumbs in bottom of pan for crust.
Add half of whip cream, then all of blueberry pie filling.
Put rest of whip cream and then rest of the crumbs. Store in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° in pie shells.
Bake low (300° to 325°) until thick, about 45 minutes.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Chop carrots, onion and green pepper; cook carrots until tender and leave onion and green pepper raw.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil; cool sauce and pour over carrots.
Add onion and green pepper; refrigerate.

title: berry dip
directions: Mix 1/2 of whipped topping and orange peel in small bowl.
Mix remaining whipped topping, strawberries and yogurt in small bowl. Dip with whole strawberries, peaches, melon slices and pound cake cubes into mixture.
Makes 5 1/4 cups.
Store leftover dip in refrigerator.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together and drain.
In large casserole dish or crock-pot, mix brown sugar, white sugar, ketchup, barbecue sauce, pepper, mustard, chili powder and salt.
Then add bacon and hamburger to mixture.
Add all beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or cook in crock-pot slowly all day or on high for 2 to 3 hours.

title: mexican muffins
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add seasoning mix and water.
Simmer 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Place muffins on cookie sheet; top with meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat together sugar, pumpkin, oil, eggs, flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat for 2 minutes; add nuts and coconut.
Bake in a greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: amish peanut brittle
directions: Cook all ingredients except for soda until a golden brown. Take off burner and add soda.
Pour out in buttered tin and let it get hard.
Break into pieces.

title: greek salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, toss together endive and lettuce. Mound into 6 individual salad plates.
Arrange lamb or beef, tomatoes, Feta cheese, olives and onion atop greens.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Flatten in crisscross with floured fork.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, vanilla, oil, sugar and zucchini until well blended. Stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: diatetic banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar-free made pudding, sour cream and Cool Whip. Put layer of pudding in bottom of bowl, then graham crackers, banana and rest of pudding.

title: coconut dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: manapua
directions: Mix the first
5 ingredients together; let stand for 10 minutes.
Place 1
rounded	tablespoonful of filling in center of roll.
Pinch edges	together
to seal.
Place on wax paper, then onto cookie sheet, 1
inch apart.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread in bottom the coconut and pecans.
Prepare German chocolate cake mix as directed.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix cream cheese, oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spoon atop cake mix evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crock-pot ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer in halves the ham, potatoes and onions in crock-pot. Salt and pepper; sprinkle on cheese.
Pour soup over top of all this.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook, covered, in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours on low, or for 4 hours on high.

title: texas fudge cake
directions: Boil oil, cocoa and water.
In separate bowl, mix sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour boiled mixture over second mixture and beat.
Pour in greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot hamburger vegetable stew
directions: Brown hamburger, stirring until crumbly. Layer vegetables in crock-pot in order listed, seasoning each layer with salt and pepper. Spoon browned hamburger over celery. Mix soup and water in bowl; mix well. Pour over hamburger.
Cook, covered, on low 6 to 8 hours or on high 2 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: nanimo bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate
and butter together over hot water.
Cool slightly. In medium
bowl
beat
egg
until
frothy.
Stir
in chocolate mixture and
sugar.
Add flour and pecans, stirring until well blended.
Turn
into pan and bake 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly on rack.

title: golden frosting
directions: Brown margarine over gentle heat.
Stir in sugar gradually, adding cream as necessary.
Beat in vanilla extract.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread on cake.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Bring strawberries, sugar, cornstarch and water to a boil. Continue to boil for 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.
Mix pudding and milk together and let it set for 5 minutes.
Mix Cool Whip with pudding mixture.
Line an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spread half of pudding mixture over crackers and place another layer of crackers on top.
Spread remainder of pudding on and line again with crackers on top.
Spread strawberry mixture on top of crackers.
Store in refrigerator.

title: elaine's margaritas
directions: Place ingredients in blender.
Fill remainder of blender with ice and blend at high speed until smooth.
Add a little water if necessary.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Stir in egg yolk and vanilla, add flour and cinnamon; mix well.
Spread dough in greased pan (11 x 17-inch), pressing with hands until even.
Spread unbeaten egg white over top, then sprinkle pecans over it and press into dough (lightly).
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
Cut in bars while hot and place on brown paper to cool.

title: sweet and sour slaw(serves 2)
directions: Shred cabbage; mix with peppers and onions.
Mix all other ingredients, then combine with cabbage mixture.
Add dressing to slaw and mix thoroughly.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in tube pan at 300° until done.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat milk until it peaks. Dissolve lemon jello in hot water. Cool before beating milk, but not set. Add lemon mixture to beaten milk, then cream cheese which has been mixed together with sugar. Beat well. Add melted margarine to cracker crumbs (save a little dry crumbs for top). Put in 9 x 12 pan. Pour milk mixture on top of cracker crumbs and top with dry crumbs. Refrigerate. Deliciously light and fluffy.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Blend sugar and shortening; then flour.
Add vanilla and nuts. Roll into small balls (a little larger than the size of a walnut).
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 300° for 45 minutes.
When cool, roll again in confectioners sugar.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar, flour and cheese.
Place in baking dish (2-quart).
Sprinkle with crackers.
Pour over melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Wonderful side dish with ham.

title: crisp belgian waffles
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in an electric blender container; process until smooth.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; process until smooth, scraping side of blender container as necessary.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Crumble corn bread and dried bread in a large mixing bowl. Add chicken broth and cream of chicken soup. Stir thoroughly. Add in chopped onions and boiled eggs. Mix again, then add sage and black pepper. Taste; you might need to add more sage. If dressing is too dry, add more broth. Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: seven layer vegetable salad
directions: Layer vegetables in the order listed in a 2-quart bowl. Spread mayonnaise evenly on top.
Sprinkle salad with remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Cover tightly and chill for 8 hours.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: welsh rabbit
directions: Shred cheese and melt on low heat.
Stir in milk, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Either dip cubes or pour over cubes.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles and rinse well.
Cut into chunks.
Put into bowl or container.
Add celery seed, cinnamon and vinegar.
Over this pour sugar (leave sugar on top).
Keep in refrigerator 2 to 3 days.
Now ready to eat.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar and egg yolks.
Then mix cream, soda and baking powder.
Combine both mixtures.
Add milk, oil or butter and egg whites, beaten stiff.
Add enough flour to stiffen and cut.
Bake at 300° for about 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly tanned.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables; add soup, sliced
eggs,
pimentos and cheese.
Mix and pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle
with
bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese; stir with fork. Add Jell-O and fruit. Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 5 to 6 hours or overnight. Serves 8 to 10.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Coat pecan halves lightly with mayonnaise or salad dressing. Bake at 325 - 350 until golden brown. Cool. Store in air tight container.

title: hot tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 3 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.
Mugs take
heaping teaspoons.
Makes 50 cups hot tea.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, milk and cinnamon and beat well.
Dip bread in batter and fry.
When cooked, sift powdered sugar on top. Serve with glass of cold milk.

title: easy italian sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and onion in 10-inch skillet, stirring frequently, until sausage is brown; drain.
Rinse beans with cold water to separate.
Stir in macaroni, sauce mix, beans, hot water, olives and garlic powder.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until beans are tender; remove from heat.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: texas chili
directions: In large kettle, brown meat; add onion.
Cook and stir until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: cheese pudding(traditional thanksgiving hollingsworth dish)
directions: Grease square pan.
Line with crackers.
Add layer of cheese, keep layering, ending with crackers on top.
Mix egg, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over crackers/cheese.
Set 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until firm.

title: pear cake
directions: Pour sugar over pears.
Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: empty cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until fluffy.
Beat in sugar.
Beat in yolks.
By hand slowly add flour.
Bake in 9-inch spring-form pan (greased) at 350° for 1/2 hour or until done.
When cake is cool, cut top off and pull out middle of cake.
Melt butter and chocolate chips.
Add Amaretto and nuts.
Mix in cake middle.
When mixed, put back in cake; add top and frost with whipped cream.

title: prune muffins
directions: Mix together egg, buttermilk and sugar.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and add.
Gently fold in oatmeal and prunes.
Add shortening.
Stir as little as possible.
Fill greased muffin pans about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.
I usually double this recipe as they freeze so well.
You can sour milk by heating it slightly and adding 1 1/3 tablespoons vinegar.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all vegetables in colander.
Put drained vegetables in bowl.
Heat sugar, oil, vinegar and spices until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over vegetables.
Place sliced onion and green pepper on top.
Let set overnight.

title: creamy chicken broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in water and add chicken bouillon granules and stir to dissolve.
Add onion, mushrooms, milk, salt, garlic and poultry seasoning.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken, rice and broccoli and salad dressing.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes before serving.

title: night-before broccoli casserole
directions: Combine drained broccoli, pimentos, onion and celery and toss well.
Stir in undiluted soup, sour cream and cheese and mix well. Pour into casserole dish and smooth top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight if desired.
To bake, sprinkle top with crumbs or stuffing mix and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or microwave 15 minutes on High or until bubbly, then run under the broiler to brown on top.
Increase conventional oven baking time by 10 minutes if casserole was refrigerated.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until done.
Drain and mash.
Add grated carrot and sour cream.
Mix well. Melt margarine and add to herb season mix.
Mix well.
Line bottom of Pyrex dish with 1/2 of season mix mixture.
Pour squash mixture on top of season mix. Top with remaining 1/2 season mix and bake at 325° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip brownie cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside.
Beat butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Set aside.

title: spicy applesauce cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Blend in egg and applesauce.
Sift together flour, salt, cloves, cinnamon, allspice and baking powder.
Add alternately with the baking soda which has been dissolved in the hot water to the applesauce mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: most moist banana bread
directions: Mix very well in a large bowl the sugar, mashed bananas and beaten egg.
Sift and mix in the dry ingredients.
Add melted butter, vanilla and nuts.
Mix very well.
Bake in a greased pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Don't cover until completely cooled.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugars and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well so oil doesn't separate.
Add flour, mixed with cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Stir in rice cereal, oats, coconut and nuts.

title: turtles
directions: Melt the caramels in double boiler. Add the canned milk. Stir to keep from getting hard. Lay 3 pecans on well buttered cookie sheet and drop large spoonfuls of caramel on top. Refrigerate overnight. Melt the Hershey bars and wax in double boiler. Dip mixture in chocolate. Cool.

title: manicotti casserole(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cheeses, egg whites, milk, parsley and oregano.
Spoon into uncooked shells.
Coat bottom of baking pan with thin layer of spaghetti sauce.
Place stuffed shells on sauce and cover with remaining sauce.
Bake 1 hour or until shells are soft.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and nuts.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Fold in whipped cream; fold into apple mixture.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: roasted vegetable salad
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Grease a large baking sheet.
Spread the eggplant and squash slices out in an even layer on the prepared baking sheet.
Place the cloves of garlic off to one side of the pan, so you can find them later.
Bake for 15 minutes in the preheated oven While the vegetables roast, whisk together the red wine vinegar, balsamic vinegar, olive oil, and lemon juice in a large serving bowl.
Season with oregano, parsley, salt and pepper. Remove the garlic cloves from the oven, and chop or mash.
Whisk the garlic into the dressing.
Set aside.
Remove the vegetables from the oven, and stir the squash and eggplant.
Layer the asparagus, red onion, and red bell pepper over the top of the eggplant and squash.
Return to the oven, and bake for another 15 to 20 minutes, or until the asparagus is tender but still bright green.
When the vegetables are cooked through and slightly toasted, remove them from the oven, and place them in the bowl with the dressing.
Stir to coat evenly.
Taste and adjust salt and pepper if necessary.
Chill for a few hours to marinate the vegetables.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Let stand at room temperature, 4 hours
or
more.
Dip onion rings, fritters, etc. and fry.

title: rice dressing
directions: Measure 1 1/2 cups raw rice and cook in separate pot.

title: cheddar-raisin muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in cheese and raisins.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased and floured muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Yield: 14 muffins.

title: lemon-lime sherbet
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt in large bowl; stir until sugar is completely dissolved.
Gradually add combined juices and lemon peel to milk, stirring constantly (mixture may appear curdled at this stage, but final product is not affected).
Stir in food coloring. Chill.
Freeze in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's directions.
Makes approximately 2 quarts.

title: refrigerator cole slaw
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and cook until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Cover the prepared vegetables with cooled brine.
Store in covered dish in refrigerator overnight before serving.
Drain portions as served.
Will keep several days.

title: tangy rhubarb sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove cinnamon stick.
May be spooned over ham 15 minutes before end of cooking time or eat and enjoy as a sauce or over ice cream.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, until brown.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Combine margarine and cracker crumbs; blend well.
Spoon half of the crumbs into a shallow, 2-quart casserole dish and cover with chicken.
Combine sour cream, soup, broth, salt and pepper; blend well.
Pour over chicken and top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Put dates into boiling water and let set. Mix sugar, Miracle Whip, flour, soda and vanilla. Add date mixture; mix well. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Sprinkle top with nuts and chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine pasta, tomatoes, broccoli and black beans; set aside.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Grease large tube/Bundt pan with 2 teaspoons of oil and set aside. In large bowl, mix popcorn, M&M's and peanuts. In small saucepan, melt butter, oil and marshmallows, stirring constantly. When melted, pour over popcorn mixture and stir to combine. Pour into greased pan, pressing down to fit. Cover with foil to keep moist and let stand until firm, 3 to 4 hours.

title: 10-minute peanut brittle
directions: Microwave the sugar, Karo and salt on High 5 minutes.
Stir in the peanuts; microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes, until lightly browned.
Stir in the butter or margarine, vanilla and baking soda.
Stir until light and fluffy.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness on large, well buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool at room temperature.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: dilled garden dip
directions: In blender container, combine cottage cheese and lemon juice. Cover; blend 3 to 5 minutes at medium speed or until smooth. Stir in carrot, onion, parsley, dill, sugar and pepper.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetable dippers.

title: oreo pie
directions: Set out ice cream 15 minutes before making pies.
Crumble 1/2 of Oreo cookies and stir into softened ice cream.
Spread mixture into pie shells.
Crumble remaining cookies and sprinkle on top. Swirl chocolate syrup over cookies.
Refreeze before serving.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in heavy saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil for approximately 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool and beat until right consistency for spreading.
Frost tops and sides of three 9-inch layers.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon and sugar.
Blend oleo, brown sugar, flour and rolled oats. Spread over the apples.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve plain or with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: veggie-cole slaw
directions: Chop all veggies real small or use food processor.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Cook together until thick the sugar, water and cornstarch. Add jello; cool.
Then stir in berries.
Put in baked pie shell. Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Put all ingredients (except sausage) into boiling water about 4 hours or until beans are tender.
Cut up sausage 30 minutes before serving and put in mixture.
Serve over Minute rice.
Serve with garlic bread and salad or cole slaw for a complete meal!

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll out.
Let dry about 20 minutes. Cut.
Drop in boiling broth.
Cook until done.

title: cook's fish omelet
directions: In a small bowl, blend eggs, milk
and pepper.
Put margarine in a 10-inch skillet and melt over medium heat.
Pour eggs into skillet.
Cook until eggs are set (about 5 minutes). Sprinkle fish and cheese over half of the omelet.
With a spatula, carefully fold other half over filling.
Cook until cheese melts (1 to 2 minutes).
Makes 2 servings.

title: veg-all supreme
directions: Drain Veg-All; combine all ingredients except buttered crumbs. Put into flat or round 3-quart casserole, buttered.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.
tags: regular size cream of chicken soup

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: While broccoli is thawing in 1 cup of water that has been brought to a boil, saute onion and celery in butter. Add soup and soup can of milk to onion and celery, then add Cheez Whiz. Simmer for a minute or so, then add thawed broccoli and rice and seasoning. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a moderate oven.
Makes 10 generous servings and can be made ahead of time.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with Cool Whip.
Add pie filling.
Stir remaining ingredients together.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in nuts, chips or candy.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in 350° oven until dry, at least 1 hour, but can be "forgotten" for hours.

title: marinated peas
directions: Combine and bring to a boil the first five ingredients.
Let cool and mix with other ingredients.
Chill this overnight.

title: easy pot roast with gravy
directions: Place roast in baking bag.
Pour soup over top of roast. Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Close bag and place in pan.
Bake at 200° for 3 to 4 hours, depending on roast size.
Vegetables may be added to bag with roast if desired.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle and cook slowly until tender and slightly thickened. Cover loosely and stir often to prevent sticking. Pour into hot sterile jars, filling 1-inch from lids. Store in cool dark place. Makes 4 quarts.

title: nacho dip
directions: Use a crock-pot or slow cooker.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Make a well in mixture and add remaining ingredients, except nuts. Mix until smooth and add nuts. Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.
Remove from pans and place on rack to cool.

title: honey buns
directions: Roll biscuits in brown sugar and cinnamon. Stand on sides in flat pan.
Pour more butter on.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes and turn out.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm with French bread (cut into dipping pieces).

title: buttermilk crunch chicken
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; set aside.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Combine eggs and buttermilk. Dip chicken in egg mixture and dredge in flour mixture, coating well.
Place in a baking dish, turning once to coat with butter. Bake chicken at 350° for 30 minutes or well done.

title: turkey casserole (light)
directions: Combine rice and water, bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until water is absorbed.
In large skillet, saute mushrooms in margarine.
Stir in flour.
Add milk, bouillon and pepper.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add turkey, water chestnuts and rice.
Mix and pour into a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Cover and bake about 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 6 servings; 197 calories, 7 grams of fat and 40 mg. cholesterol.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine flour and shortening in a medium bowl, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in cheese and milk.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead lightly 3-4 times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness, cut into rounds with biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10-12 minutes.
Yield:
one dozen.

title: chocolate yogurt fudge
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In it, combine sugar, yogurt, cocoa and corn syrup; cook and stir over medium-high heat, until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil.
Continue cooking over medium-high heat to 234°, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; do not stir.
Cool to lukewarm (110°).
Add nuts; beat vigorously until fudge becomes very thick and just starts to lose gloss. Immediately spread in a buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Score while warm; cut when cool.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: dottie's hot vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; drain.
Put into casserole dish.
Add salt and garlic salt.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Trim edges of bread.
Beat egg yolk until soft.
Spread on bread.
Roll bread into roll slices.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 1 stick butter (melted) and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Dip bread sticks into mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cook at 15 minutes at 400°.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Add flour. Roll small portions of dough 1/8-inch or 1/4-inch thick on floured cloth or board.
Cut with assorted cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: gob cake
directions: Add
all
ingredients.	Beat
on high speed for about 6 minutes.
Pour
on	2 greased and floured cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.	Cool.

title: meat sauce for spaghetti
directions: Brown beef; add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir frequently.
Serve over spaghetti.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: rolls
directions: Mix water, 4 cups flour, dry milk, sugar and salt, then add softened butter and yeast.
Cover and rise for 45 minutes.
Add next 4 cups flour; let rise again for 45 minutes.
This is a very soft dough.
Pour out onto a heavily floured surface.
Roll into shapes.
Place on greased pans and let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels, margarine and milk on low heat.
Pour this over baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over caramel layer. For next layer, pour remaining cake batter on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken with fruit and rice pilaf
directions: Flour chicken with dry ingredients then dip in margarine. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Add fruit.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: chinese stir-fry
directions: Use large pan or wok for best results.
Heat oil on high until hot (not boiling).
Turn heat down to medium-high.
First, add chopped ginger to oil and let it saut for 1 minute.
Then add garlic and saut for an additional minute.
Turn heat back up to high and add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir constantly to ensure the mixture gets cooked by rotating the vegetables.
Do this 4 to 5 minutes or until desired texture and taste.
Turn heat down to medium and add soy sauce to taste and continue to stir for another minute.

title: berry pork chops
directions: Wash cranberries; crush coarsely and mix with marmalade and cloves.
Cut a deep pocket in one side of each chop.
Fill pockets with marmalade mixture.
Place chops in a well greased baking pan. Spoon 1 tablespoon honey over each.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes until mostly glazed.

title: chocolate ball cookies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly. Add sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually blend this into chocolate mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Chill dough several hours.
Form into small balls; roll in confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: friendship bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Drain next morning.
Add 2 quarts of cold water; salt to taste.
Add ham (cut in small cubes).
Simmer 2 hours.
Add onion, garlic, tomatoes and lemon juice.
Simmer 2 more hours.
Serve with cornbread or jalapeno cornbread.

title: golden fruit punch
directions: Pour juices into a gallon container.
Add sugar and enough water to fill.
Mix well and place in refrigerator and chill for several hours.
At serving time, pour juice mixture into punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Juice mixture can be frozen in a ring mold with mint leaves, lemon or lime slices and used to chill punch when serving.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Top with paprika and a little extra cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cake delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl for 4 minutes at medium speed. Bake at 350° in well-greased, floured pan (9 x 13-inch) for 35 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Let butter soften; then whip it in a mixer with powdered sugar (add sugar according to how sweet you want).
When it is whipped, add strawberries.
Excellent with Ritz crackers.

title: apple sour cream pie
directions: In a larger mixing bowl, add apples, eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, mace and coriander.
Combine dry ingredients to apple mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Add the top shell. Seal and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mash cheeses thoroughly. Mix together. Pour in pecans, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, pepper and Tabasco. Shape into ball and sprinkle with paprika. Chill several hours before eating.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix and pour into a Pam-sprayed quiche dish or pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (browned on top).

title: gail's vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well and stir in sugar, beating well.
Add condensed milk, evaporated milk and vanilla, then add the Cool Whip.
Pour into churn and add enough milk to finish filling churn.
Freeze.

title: bake salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, pouring broth into a small bowl.
Add cracker crumbs to the liquid and set aside.
remove bones and skin from salmon as desired and crumble fish into a medium bowl.
Add eggs and cornmeal; mix well.
Add softened crackers to mixture.
Shape into patties and place onto a foil-lined (spray with nonstick cooking spray) baking sheet and bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until brown as you like.
Yield:
about 20 patties.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. Preheat oven to 350°. In a mixing bowl, cream margarine until fluffy. Add sugar and beat well. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crosscut (bread and butter)(usda bulletin)
directions: Wash cucumbers and drain.
Slice unpeeled into 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices and discard ends.
Add onions and garlic.
Add salt and mix well.
Cover with crushed ice and let stand 3 hours.
Drain well and remove the garlic.
Combine sugar, spices and vinegar and heat just to boiling.
Add drained cucumbers and onion slices and heat 5 minutes.
Pack hot pickles loosely into clean, hot pint jars to 1/2 inch of top.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water for 5 minutes. (Start to count processing time as soon as water in canner returns to boiling.)
Remove jars and complete seals if necessary.
Set jars upright to cool.
Sugar may be reduced to 4 cups if a less sweet pickle is desired.
USDA recommends that all pickles be processed in water bath cooker for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet red pepper marmalade
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Finely chop peppers in blender. Put in colander and add salt.
Let drain for 1 hour.
Boil sugar, vinegar and water for 5 minutes.
Add peppers; cook slowly until thickened, about 1 1/2 hours.
Pour, while hot, into jelly jars and seal immediately with hot, melted paraffin.
Spread over cream cheese and serve on crackers.

title: aunt mildred's blue ribbon red velvet pound cake
directions: *Use 1/2 cup cocoa for chocolate cake and omit red food coloring.

title: sweet and sour sauce on cream cheese
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients
and let chill a few hours.
Pour over cream cheese.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: lemon-basil carrot bundles
directions: Cut carrots into 80 (2 x 1/4-inch) strips.
Combine carrots and next 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat 6 to 8 minutes or until carrots are crisp-tender.
Remove from heat.
Place carrots in a shallow bowl.
Reserve cooking liquid in saucepan.
Add basil, lemon rind and oil to cooking liquid; set aside.
Trim white portion from green onions (reserve for another use).
Place green onion tops in a large bowl; add boiling water to cover.
Drain immediately and rinse under cold running water.
Cut tops into 20 narrow strips.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Set aside. Cream butter and add 3/4 cup sugar. Beat well.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix meat, taco or chili mix and can of tomatoes.
Simmer while rice is cooking according to package directions.
Add beans to meat mixture last 5 minutes.
Place by layers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer: rice, meat and cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with chips, lettuce and tomato.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Coarsely chop graham crackers with Food Chopper.
Combine graham crackers, butter and sugar.
Press into bottom and up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine whipped topping, pudding and sour cream in Batter Bowl with 10-inch whisk.
Pour half of filling over the crust.
Slice bananas with the egg slicer.
Layer bananas on top.
Pour remaining filling over bananas.
Finely chop pecans with the Food Chopper and sprinkle over top.
Sets immediately but can be refrigerated to chill.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift flour.
Cut or mix in shortening.
Add sugar and sweet potatoes.
Stir in buttermilk.
Use a little more flour if necessary to make a stiff dough.
Toss dough on floured board and knead lightly.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cutter or roll out with hands.
Bake at 450° until golden brown. Butter biscuits while warm and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Whip sugar, peanut butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Blend in gelatin until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend thoroughly. Pour into pie crust; refrigerate until served (1 to 2 hours).

title: date and nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda and let stand until cool.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour into paper lined greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: favorite krinkle top cookie
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add molasses and egg. Add dry sifted ingredients and mix well. Roll in small balls, dip in sugar and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: wagon wheel tuna bake(serves 4)
directions: In a 9-inch round baking dish, combine soup, rice, milk, lemon and tuna. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes; stir. Arrange broccoli spoke fashion on rice mixture. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 10 minutes more.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Drain vegetables and mix together with soup in same skillet.
Add just enough water to keep moist. Simmer about 10 minutes.
Pour dressing on the top.
Put lid on and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: poulet au vin blanc(chicken with white wine; serves 4)
directions: Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Shake off excess flour and reserve.

title: pink stuff salad
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Ready to serve in 1 hour for salad or dessert.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Combine flour, paprika and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a bag.
Add chicken and shake until well coated.
Brown chicken on both sides in butter and oil in a large skillet.
Add sherry. Cover and simmer for about 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: tropical fruit delight
directions: Cook gelatin, tapioca pudding mix, sugar and orange juice over low heat until thick, approximately 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and place in serving bowl.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Best if chilled overnight.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight or 1 to 2 hours before cooking.
Put ham and beans in large cooking pot.
Cover with water.
Keep covered with water.
When beans begin to get soft, add onion and carrot. Let simmer until done.
Soup can be heated again if you have any left over.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix egg yolks, reserving egg whites, flour and sugar-cinnamon. Beat thoroughly, then add vanilla, milk and butter.
Mix thoroughly again.
Cook slowly over low heat, stirring constantly until desired thickness.
Rotate layering wafers and bananas in ovenproof, deep dish or pan.
Pour first mixture over wafers and bananas.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat butter until soft.
Add brown sugar and blend.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, granulated sugar, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and oatmeal.
Mix tightly in batter. Add walnuts, chocolate chunks, lemon juice and vanilla.
Do not overmix.
Scoop cookies into 3-ounce balls and place on greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour bread pan.
Mix oil, egg and sugar well.
Add the other ingredients.
Pour into bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat and bake for 13 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread over cooled rolls.
Sprinkle shredded sharp cheese over mixture.
Garnish with your favorite fresh veggies.

title: no kneading yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; let set 12 hours before using.
Keep in refrigerator.
To use, oil hands, pinch off walnut size balls of dough.
Place on baking pan; let set 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: In 4 quart pan cook vegetables in margarine until tender. Stir in flour until well mixed.
Stir in chicken broth, one can at a time slowly.
Stir and cook over medium heat until liquid boils. Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Chop up Velveeta.
Stir until smooth.
Add pepper.
Serve with hot crusty bread.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: party meatballs
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in the cup of water; mix all ingredients together; add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Roll into tiny balls.
Brown until very crisp in hot oil.
These may be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix well all the ingredients and make into small meatballs. Lay in shallow pan.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix butter and corn flakes; set aside.
Mix all remaining ingredients together and put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with the corn flake mixture and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked beef and noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water (salted) 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain well.
While noodles cook, saute beef and onions.
Add spices, mushrooms and 1 cup cheese.
Pour cooked noodles and meat mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Top with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream together margarine and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add flour and mix.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs until frothy; add 1 cup brown sugar and mix until smooth.
Mix in pecans, coconut, 2 tablespoons flour, vanilla and salt.
Combine well and pour over crust.
Continue to bake at 350° for 20 more minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with sugar.

title: mocha truffle cookies
directions: In
a
large
saucepan,
melt margarine and the 1/2 cup chocolate
pieces
over
low heat.	Remove from heat.
Stir in coffee
crystals;
cool
5	minutes.
Stir in sugars, eggs and vanilla.
In a medium mixing bowl combine flour, cocoa powder, baking
powder
and
salt.	Stir into coffee mixture.
Stir in the 1 cup chocolate pieces.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoons onto lightly
greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Let
cool
minute before removing from sheet. Makes 30 cookies.

title: hawaiian grilled chicken
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a shallow dish or heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag.
Add chicken; cover or seal and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Add eggs and Ricotta cheese.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add baking powder and baking soda to flour. Sift.
Add to other ingredients, gradually.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.
Make icing with 10x sugar, a drop of milk and a drop of vanilla.

title: danish puff coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure first cup of flour into bowl.
Cut in 1 stick of butter.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of water and mix with fork.
Round into a ball and divide in half.
Pat dough into 2 long (12 x 3-inch) strips.
Do this on ungreased baking sheet about 3 inches apart.
Mix the second amount of butter and water.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add almond flavoring and remove from heat.
Stir in flour immediately to keep it from lumping.
When smooth and thick, add 1 egg at a time, beating until smooth.
Divide in half and spread on half evenly over each piece of pastry.
Bake about 60 minutes until topping is crisp and browned.
Frost with powdered sugar glaze using almond extract and sprinkle generously with sliced almonds.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until done.
Skin and mash.
Measure all ingredients into a bowl.
Blend together.
Pour into a 9-inch deep dish pie shell and bake in a moderate oven until done.

title: beef chunks in sour cream
directions: Roll beef cubes in flour; brown in shortening.
Add onions and brown.
Add mushrooms, water and spices.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 1 3/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally during cooking.
Stir in sour cream and heat through. Serve over noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef panzerotti
directions: Unroll pizza crust on lightly greased 15 x 10 inch baking sheet.
Arrange roast beef slices lengthwise in the center of dough.
Spread pizza sauce on top of beef.
Layer cheese slices on top; sprinkle peppers over cheese.
Fold sides of dough over filling; pinch edges and ends to seal.
Bake in 425 degree oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Cut into 8 thick slices. Serve with additional warm pizza sauce and salad if desired.

title: chopped apple pie(makes 2)
directions: Cream first 7 ingredients.
Stir in apples.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: granny's spruill's gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Roll out dough into a ball.
Dip into sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
(Do not overbake.)

title: yogurt-cucumber soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour about 1/3 of mixture into an electric blender; blend until smooth.
Pour into a pitcher or bowl; repeat procedure with remaining mixture. Cover and chill several hours.
Garnish with cucumber slices and fresh dill weed, if desired.
Yield: about 5 cups.

title: mississippi mud pie - baked chocolate pie shell
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat at low speed until well blended, about 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes and fold in instant coffee and Cool Whip.
Place in pie shell. Freeze about 6 hours.
Remove and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add nuts and raisins.
Spray cake pans with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 375°.
Make 4 layers.

title: texas hash
directions: Set bread slices out first to let the air harden them.
Heat oil in skillet.
Saute pepper and onions until tender.
Add hamburger and cook until pink is gone from meat.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle melted butter on bread slices and crumble bread over mixture.
Bake at 350° until bread crumbs are brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and serve with chips or crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until pie is custard consistency.

title: delicious chocolate cake from a mix
directions: Grease and flour large Bundt pan.
Mix together ingredients, then fold in chocolate bits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and unmold.

title: fettuccine alfredo(fat-free)
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring with wire whisk until blended.
Cook 8 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in cream cheese and cook 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup Parmesan cheese, stirring constantly until it melts.
Pour over hot cooked fettuccine; toss well to coat.

Top with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, fresh parsley and pepper. Yields 4 servings (55 1 c.); calories 345 (25% from fat), protein 16.8 g, (sat 4.4 mond 2.7 g poly 1.4 g), carbohydrate 46.7 g, fiber 2.3 g, cholesterol 18 mg, iron 2.3 mg, sodium 401 mg and calcium 333 mg.

title: peanut marshmallow crunchies
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir constantly until marshmallows are melted and well blended.
Heat 2 or 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press into pan with fingers moistened with water.
Cut into squares when cool. Makes 24 squares.

title: can't fail divinity
