directions: Boil sugar, water and salt until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Place Marshmallow Creme in mixing bowl and stir in hot syrup.
Continue stirring until slightly stiff.
Fold in nuts or fruit and vanilla.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Yields 24 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: orange bread(bread machine)
directions: Place all ingredients except orange peel in machine according to manufacturer's directions.
Add the orange peel about 5 minutes before the end of the second kneading cycle.
Yield:
1 (1 1/2 pound) loaf.

title: mango cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 5 inch baking pan. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and beans together.
When ready to serve, add dressing and Fritos; toss.

title: evangeline's chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked 9 inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: supper casserole
directions: The dough for our Thin Crust Homemade Pizza may also be used for breadsticks.
Depending on the desired length, pinch off pieces of dough and roll into breadstick shapes.
Brush each piece with olive oil and roll in seasoned salt.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes or until crisp and brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix chicken, pimientos, water chestnuts, almonds, m.s.g., celery salt, pepper, lemon juice, mayonnaise and chicken soup. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with onion rings and bake another 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: banana split pie
directions: Bake and cool crust.
Cream together powdered sugar, softened butter, egg, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Place in refrigerator to firm slightly.
Combine Cool Whip, fruit, pecans and milk; spread on top of powdered sugar mixture.
Garnish with halved cherries.
Makes a light dessert that tops off a big meal deliciously.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Make chocolate cake as directed on the box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool.
Split lengthwise, giving two 13-inch layers.
Mix in a saucepan to a hard boil, sugar and milk for 5 minutes.
Add marshmallows until dissolved and then add coconut. Stir well.
Spread mixture between layers and over the top.
Pour on icing.

title: dixie beef stew
directions: Combine grapefruit juice, salt and garlic in large bowl.
Add beef cubes and refrigerate overnight.
Drain beef, reserving marinade.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in greased casserole dish, except corn flakes and melted 1/4 cup oleo.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Combine with shortening mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel krispy marshmallows
directions: Melt margarine, caramels and milk together in double boiler over hot water.
Roll each marshmallow in caramel mixture, then in Rice Krispies.

title: party-going pork chops
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan.
Brown chops.
Place onion and pepper rings on top of each pork chop.
Pour soup over and around. Cover and cook on low heat for 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake in layers according to package directions.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour in dish with melted margarine.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: taco puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In skillet, brown and crumble sausage. Remove skillet from heat and allow to cool for a few minutes. Remove excess fat.
In mixing bowl, combine sausage and remaining ingredients.
Form into small balls, about 1-inch in diameter. Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until puffs are lightly brown.
Makes 24 puffs.

title: veggie flake pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions (angel hair takes about 4 minutes).
Drain and rinse.
Return to same pot.
Add margarine, tossing until melted.
Add yogurt, Parmesan cheese, carrot, parsley, salt and pepper.
Toss until all pasta is coated. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raise donuts
directions: Pour hot milk over butter, sugar and salt.
Crumble yeast into lukewarm water to soften.
Cool milk to lukewarm and add yeast. Add eggs.
Beat in flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Form into balls and place in oiled bowl.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: mexican green salad
directions: Brown
meat
and
drain well.
Set aside to cool.
Chop and toss greens.
Add beans, cheese, Fritos, meat and dressing just before serving.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except onion rings and cheese.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle onion rings and cheese over the top.
You can also add 1/2 cup onions (chopped) and 1 cup tuna (rinsed and drained).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings. Top with slivered almonds the last 10 minutes.

title: peanut buttered pork loin
directions: Place pork loins in shallow roasting pan; season with salt and pepper.
Insert meat thermometer.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until thermometer reads 170°.
Meanwhile, combine orange juice and peanut butter.
When thermometer reads 170° brush sauce on roast and continue baking and basting 15 to 20 minutes more.
Serves 15.

title: banana fudge pie
directions: Prepare one pie crust according to package directions for filled one crust pie.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: chicken chunks
directions: Cut
chicken into chunks.
Beat eggs and mix with water. Combine flour, paprika, seasoning and salt.
Mix to make a batter. Dip chicken chunks in batter and deep fry for 3 to 5 minutes. Drain on paper towel.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Combine in a small saucepan; bring to boil.
Add 2 (6-ounce) cans of mushroom crowns, drained.
Simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
Chill in covered bowl several hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain. Makes 2 cups.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Bring to a boil vinegar, sugar and oil until dissolved well.
Let cool and pour over vegetables. Mix and store in refrigerator.
Lasts for several days.

title: fruit dip
directions: Lay pecan halves on foil lined pan; cover with 3 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle salt to taste.
Put in oven at 300° and bake for 15 minutes.
Turn off heat; leave in oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: crab-shrimp salad
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Dice each slice.
Add onion,
chopped fine, and hard-boiled eggs, chopped.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Add shrimp, crab, celery and mayonnaise and mix well. Cover and let stand 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.

title: grandma's special pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
Slice 1 inch thick.
Place back in jar.
Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over pickles.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Scrumptious!

title: corn crab cakes
directions: Combine the crabmeat, corn, onion and bell pepper in mixing bowl and toss well.
In another bowl, combine the mayonnaise with the mustard and cayenne pepper.
Stir into the crabmeat mixture and add salt and pepper to taste.
Using a rubber spatula, gently fold in the egg and 1/4 cup of bread crumbs.
Form the crab mixture into 8 patties.
Carefully coat the patties with the remaining cup of bread crumbs and chill, covered, for at least 30 minutes, but no longer than a few hours.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil and 1 tablespoon butter in a medium skillet.
Cook the crab cakes over medium heat until golden on both sides, about 3 minutes per side, adding more oil and butter as necessary.
Serve immediately with tartar sauce on the side.
Makes 4 portions.

title: peaches 'n cream dessert
directions: Make a crust out of the butter and graham cracker crumbs, reserving 1/2 cup for top.
Press mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Stir a scant 1/2 cup sugar into peaches; set aside.

title: mexican platter
directions: Spread bean dip on platter; peel and mash avocado.
Mix with sour cream; put avocado mixture on bean dip; drain and layer green chilies; chop and layer onion; chop and layer olives; dice and layer tomato; sprinkle cheese on top.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, peppers and season to taste.
Dip 3 tortillas into enchilada sauce.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Add 1/4 layer beef mixture and then layer 1/4 cheese. Continue layers.
Pour extra sauce over top.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.

title: delicious punch
directions: Add water to frozen juice as on can.
Add all other juices . Just before serving, spoon in sherbet, then ginger ale.
Pour ginger ale down side of bowl.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Wash celery.
In bowl, blend cheese, peppers and chili powder. Stuff celery.

title: ham barbecues
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Add ketchup, chili sauce and barbecue sauce to first mixture.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: christmas candy
directions: Melt chocolate over medium-low heat, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in crunch.
Spread on wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator 8 to 10 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a
casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder
and
milk.
Pour mixture into casserole.
Spoon peaches and
juice into mixture (evenly).
Sweeten the peaches to taste. Be
sure you have enough juice in peaches.
If not, add a
little water.
Sprinkle sugar and spices on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange chiffon layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites with 1/3 cup sugar until thick and glossy, but not stiff.
Set aside. Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add orange juice, milk, Puritan oil and egg yolks. Mix at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Scrape bottom and sides of bowl often.
Fold egg whites into batter until well blended.
Pour into two greased and floured 8 x 1 1/2-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool 10 to 20 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix the crushed crackers, 1 stick margarine and 1/3 cup sugar. Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Then mix Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip, frozen orange juice and mandarin oranges together.
Pour over cracker mixture.
Refrigerate for 4 hours, then serve.

title: lobster soup
directions: Add rich milk to soup. Brown lobster meat in butter.
Add to soup mixture and warm slowly.
Add sherry just before taking off stove.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into about 30 balls.
Press slightly with a fork to flatten.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Cut French bread in half to expose center of bread.
Mix butter and garlic; mix well.
Spread garlic butter on both sides of bread and sprinkle with desired amount of cheese.
Bake on a cookie sheet in a 350° oven until cheese has browned, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with lasagna, spaghetti or just for an appetizer.

title: fiesta pie
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl; stir in milk.
Add remaining ingredients except salsa and sour cream; mix well.
Pour mixture into greased 9-inch microwavable pie plate.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir mixture from edge to middle.
Cover; microwave 4 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve immediately with salsa and sour cream.
Serves 6. Preparation time: 15 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add bananas and half the buttermilk.
Mix until all flour is damp. Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add remaining milk and eggs. Beat 2 minutes longer.
Fold in nuts.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Let cake cool completely.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl and mix lightly.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and chop avocados into a bowl. Mash with garlic, lemon juice and salt until mixture is smooth and creamy. Serve with Tostitos or chips. If this is prepared ahead of time, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: dago cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage, onion, water, salt and pepper for 15 minutes. Brown ground round and sausage.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir into boiled cabbage and cook until cabbage is tender.
Serve over cornbread.

title: pineapple-chocolate squares
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients until fluffy; beat in eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Divide batter; to 1/2, add nuts and chocolate; spread into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add pineapple to remaining batter; spread carefully over chocolate layer.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until done.
(Can also use 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.)
Cut in squares when cool.

title: easter breakfast
directions: Beat together the eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over the bread pieces, sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cooked cucumber sauce
directions: Boil and chill.
Add cucumbers and onions that have been thinly sliced.
Servings for 4.
Preparation time: 20 minutes.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice into casserole dish.
Heat soups and water and pour over rice.
Arrange pork chops on rice.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup.
Cover container with foil.
Bake in 325° oven for 2 hours and 15 minutes without covering.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: triple layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°
(325° for glass dish).
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine. Top evenly with coconut, then sweetened condensed milk. Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
In a small saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips with peanut butter.
Spread evenly over hot coconut layer.
Cool and then cut into bars. Store at room temperature.

title: egg substitute
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Store in refrigerator for up to 1 week in airtight container or freeze for a month. One-fourth cup represents 1 egg.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Heat together the shredded sharp Cheddar cheese and uncooked hot or mild sausage in a large saucepan; stir together with wooden spoon until cheese has melted.
Stir in the biscuit mix until smooth.
Cool, then chill for about an hour for easier handling. Form into balls about the size of a nickle or slightly larger. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove; place on paper towels to drain.
Serve warm. These sausage balls freeze beautifully after baking.
Simply place in a slow oven to heat thoroughly before serving.
Yields at least 4 dozen.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and egg.
Sift flour and all dry ingredients together.
Mix milk with molasses.
Add dry ingredients and liquid alternately.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rotel casserole
directions: Brown the ground meat and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until done, probably about 10 minutes, especially when using Minute rice.
Add more water if mixture is too dry.

title: lime salad
directions: Blend cottage cheese, mayonnaise, milk and pineapple.
Mix lime jello and boiling water together.
Chill until begins to firm.
Combine jello and other ingredients.

title: main-dish pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough and separate rolls.
Spread to cover bottom of ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Press together to form lower crust.
Bake 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, in large skillet, brown beef and onion; drain excess fat.
Stir in gravy and peas; cook until heated through.
Pour mixture into partially baked crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until crust is brown and cheese is melted.
Arrange tomato slices over pie; bake 2 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: sugared pecans
directions: In jelly roll pan, melt butter.
While melting, beat until stiff the egg whites, brown sugar and vanilla. Dump pecans into egg mixture.
Spread on buttered pan with two forks into one layer.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt butter and add onion, celery and pepper; cook until light brown.
Add all other ingredients, including cut up chicken.
Add cooked spaghetti; cook down until thick.
Put in baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Put in slow oven to melt cheese.
Makes two 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dishes.

title: irish lace cookies(makes about 9 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, salt and oatmeal.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil and drop dough by 1/2 teaspoon onto foil.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes in a 350° oven until lightly browned.
Let cool.
Remove from foil.

title: amish slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onions, green pepper and sugar together.
Set aside while making dressing.
Combine vinegar, water, celery seed, salad mustard and salt together in small saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over cabbage mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and press down in a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown. Cool.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients and beat 2 minutes. Bake 20 to 22 minutes.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a thick skillet. Add onion, pepper and celery; saute over medium heat, stirring often, until soft. Remove from heat; add peas and chestnuts and fold in pimento.
Put a layer of vegetable mixture in bottom of a 2-quart casserole. Top with undiluted soup. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until bubbling hot.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator 30 minutes. Stir and drop by spoonful into hot oil until brown.

title: hot pasta salad
directions: Saute garlic with olive oil until tender (not brown).
Mix the rest of the ingredients and add to cooked spaghetti.
Add sauteed garlic.
Mix well and serve.

title: 7 layer cookie dessert
directions: In a 13x9x2 metal pan layer the ingredients above in order shown.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes

title: swiss green beans
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in large saucepan.
Add sour cream. Stir constantly until bubbly.
Add green beans.
Spread in shallow casserole dish.
Top with grated Swiss cheese and corn flake crumbs (1/2 cup corn flakes and 2 tablespoons melted margarine).
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Mix cucumbers and onions with salt and ice in layers.
Let stand for 2 hours and drain. Mix vinegar, sugar and spices.
Heat to boiling point.
Put in cucumbers and onions after draining.
Bring to boiling again but do not boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: cauliflower broccoli sauté
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted water till crisp.
Drain and set aside, returning liquid to pan.
Return to boiling, adding more water if necessary.
Add broccoli and cook till crisp tender. Drain and keep warm.
Saute garlic in butter till golden.
Add mushrooms and saute till tender.
Add bouillon cubes, crushing to mix.
Add vegetables and soy sauce and stir fry 5 minutes to heat. Season if necessary.

title: sausage-pasta soup
directions: Remove sausage from casing.
In large saucepan over medium-high heat, brown sausage and onion.
Drain excess fat. Stir in tomatoes, broth, water and salami.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add rotini; simmer 15 minutes, or until pasta is tender.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple stuffing for roast goose
directions: Cook the apples with just enough water to keep from burning until tender; drain.
Blend all the ingredients together and mix thoroughly.
Can be used for chicken or turkey.

title: noodle kugel(a good side dish with fish or chicken.)
directions: In a large soup pot, brown sausage.
Drain off all fat.
Add remaining soup ingredients, except cabbage, being careful with salt and pepper because sausage varies in seasonings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Set yeast in cup of warm water (not too hot or cool).
Stir sugar, shortening, salt and eggs together.
Add yeast and scalded milk.
Add flour until thick enough to knead.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Knead bread.
Make 2 dozen rolls.
Make 2 loaves of bread. Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: granny's pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue baking 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center of pie comes out clean.

title: buckeyes
directions: In mixing bowl, mix softened butter and peanut butter. Gradually add powdered sugar.
Make into balls.
In double boiler, melt paraffin and add chocolate chips on low heat.
With toothpicks, dip balls into chocolate and place on wax paper. Chill for 15 minutes.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Partially freeze steak; trim fat.
Slice steak diagonally across grain into 1/4-inch strips.
Place in a zip top heavy-duty bag.
Combine wine, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and cornstarch; pour over steak.
Seal bag; shake until steak is coated.
Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours.
Combine water, honey, remaining 1 tablespoon soy sauce and red pepper.
Stir well and set aside. Coat a wok or large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add 1 teaspoon oil.
Place over medium-high heat (375°) until hot.
Add broccoli and stir-fry 4 minutes.
Remove broccoli from wok.
Set aside; keep warm.

title: diabetic old fashioned thumbprint cookies
directions: Beat together margarine, egg, vanilla and enough flour so dough is no longer sticky.
Work in nuts.
Chill until firm enough to shape (about 30 minutes).
Roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip your thumb in flour.
Press down firmly in middle of each cookie.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown on the bottoms.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with Equal.
Cool. Fill hollows with jam.
Keep refrigerated.
Calories: 98. Diabetic exchange: 1/2 bread and 1 fat.

title: meatballs in herbed sour cream
directions: Combine beef and 2 tablespoons gravy mix.
Shape into 12 meatballs.
Brown in hot oil.
Pour off excess fat.
Add water and the remaining gravy mix; mix well.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Makes 4 servings of 3 meatballs each.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° on a cookie sheet for 20 minutes.

title: yellow squash pickles
directions: Wash and slice squash.
Sprinkle with salt and set aside for 1 hour.
Bring vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Add squash, onion, green pepper and pimento; bring to a boil again.
Pack in jars.
Add mustard and celery seed to remaining juice in pan and boil.
Pour into jars.
Seal and process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not grease.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a large Pyrex dish.
Pour in rice.
Dilute soup with 1 can water.
Pour over rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice and soup.
Salt to taste.
Brown chicken in butter.
Place on top of mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, corn syrup, vinegar and salt in saucepan. Add butter; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until comes to boil.
Add cream; cook to hard ball stage.
Stir into popcorn. Butter hands and roll into balls.

title: the luck of the irish(mary's irish bread)
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes; then cover with tinfoil and bake 10 additional minutes.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Cook noodles. Combine hamburger, noodles, cheese, soup, 1 cup of water, pepper, chili sauce, pimento, salt and pepper; mix well.
Put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: belle isle ice tea
directions: In a 2-quart pitcher, combine listed ingredients.
Add ice to the top and refrigerate for about 2 hours.
It is not recommended to add more than the listed amounts of alcohol.
If you would like to make a lighter drink, add an extra 1/3 cup of Coca Cola and orange juice and reduce the alcohol to 1 1/2 shots each.

title: excitement salad
directions: Wash all fruits and vegetables.
Cut fruits and vegetables into bite size pieces.
Chop garlic.
Place all the ingredients into a covered bowl.
(For example:
a Tupperware dish with cover.)

title: green pepper steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger. Add beef. Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables. Heat oil in a large frying pan or wok. Add beef and toss over high heat until browned. Taste meat. If it is not tender, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes over low heat. Turn heat up and add vegetables. Toss vegetables until tender-crisp, about 10 minutes. Mix cornstarch and water. Add to pan. Stir and cook until thickened.

title: grandma moses tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Mix in all the dry ingredients.
Chill for about an hour, then roll out and use cookie cutters to cut cookies.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes, depending on how thick you roll them out.

title: snow cream
directions: In a big bowl, mix cream, eggs, vanilla and sugar to taste. Scrape off first inch or so of new fallen snow.
Combine with cream mixture until right texture and taste.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Eat immediately.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
In mixer bowl, beat peanut butter and shortening on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to beaten mixture and beat until well blended.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.

title: french beef au gratin
directions: Melt margarine and saute onions 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove onions from pan and brown meat well.
Return onions and any juice to pan.
In small bowl, mix flour, sugar, cumin, salt and pepper. Add to pan; stir 1 minute until bubbly.
Gradually add broth, stirring to scrape drippings from pan.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Heat broiler.
Place 1/2 cup of fettuccine in each of four 16-ounce bowls.
Divide beef mixture over pasta.
In a bowl, mix cheeses together; sprinkle evenly over beef.
Broil about 5 minutes until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: dirty rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage.
Add pepper, onion and celery. Saute until done.
Prepare Minute rice by substituting the chicken broth for the water called for on the package directions. Prepare wild rice as directed on package.
Add both rices to the sausage mix in the skillet.
Heat and serve.
Additional broth may be needed if the rice mixture is too dry.
Serves 6.

title: hot tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the chips.
Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with cheese-baking powder biscuits.

title: party potato slices
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Mix together sour cream and chives. Lightly brush both sides of potatoes with margarine; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Broil 5 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place meat in 5-quart pressure cooker.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley.
Close cover securely.
Place pressure regulator on vent pipe.
Cook 20 minutes with pressure regulator rocking slowly.
Let the pressure drop off of own accord.
Add parsley to soup just before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy oven beef stew
directions: In heavy Dutch oven or crock-pot, first layer meat, then onion, celery, carrots and potatoes.
Lay on bay leaf.
Mix salt, sugar and tapioca.
Sprinkle over.
Add Worcestershire sauce, tomatoes and water.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours for in crock-pot overnight for 8 hours on low.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: linda j's chutney dip
directions: Dice chutney.
Mix cheeses, add chutney.
Stir in onion, ginger and salt.
Better if prepared 2 days ahead of time.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: baked penne and smoked sausage
directions: Cut sausage into 1/4-inch slices and brown in skillet. Drain. Combine soup and milk in 3-quart casserole. Stir in pasta, sausage, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 cup French fried onions and peas. Bake, covered, 20 minutes or until hot. Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake 3 minutes, uncovered, until golden.

title: jerk pork fancy
directions: Mince jerk pork, using the coarsest cutter or chop it finely. Blend with chopped onion and pepper.
Add sauce.
Warm a large cooking spoon.
Pour rum into it and light.
When burning well, pour rum all over the blended mixture, shaking it until it has burned all through mixture.
Let it burn out completely, then mix the powdered ginger.
Serve with crackers like Solomon Gundy (chicken, beef).

title: chicken in red sauce
directions: Clean the chicken and burn any hair around it.
Then brush it with oil.
Warm the pan; put the chicken in and saute until it becomes rosy.
Add salt and pepper and fill it with the cheese. Put the tomatoes and the sauce with the sugar in the large pan. Cover it with water.
Cook the chicken for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: almost-french-fried onion rings(makes 2 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine bread crumbs, salt and pepper in a small, shallow bowl.
Dip each onion ring first in egg white, then in crumbs.
Place on a nonstick baking sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Blend butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour, vanilla and cream cheese.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Place in oven and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Your favorite glaze may be used or can be served plain.

title: italian meat roll
directions: Season round steak with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Marinate for 1 hour in marinade made with meat marinade, red wine and salad dressing.
Remove from marinade and spread with mixture of bread crumbs, crumbled bread, onion, celery, green pepper, garlic, olives, Parmesan cheese and listed seasonings.
Moisten mixture with marinade liquid.
Roll steak and tie with cord.
Bake in Ragu spaghetti sauce at 350°, covered, for about 1 hour.
Baste steak often with sauce.
Slice roll for serving.
Excellent with spaghetti.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eagle brand milk substitute
directions: Blend together for 1 minute.
Makes the equivalent of 1 can of milk.

title: fried rice with curried meatballs
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water until tender.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine ground pork or turkey, the bread crumbs, 1 teaspoon curry powder and the salt.
Mix and roll into 1-inch balls.
In a large nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add meatballs and brown well.
Add carrots.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in zucchini, garlic and scallions.
Cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Push vegetables and meatballs to one side of pan.
Add remaining 4 teaspoons curry powder.
Add rice and cook 5 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening.
Blend in sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour and milk, alternating and beating well.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: bologna sandwiches
directions: To the bread, add mayonnaise, mustard, lettuce, pickles, relish, cheese, etc.
Top with two, not one, slices of bologna. Put on plate; paper will do.
Add chips and enjoy.

title: russian mushroom and potato soup
directions: Saute onions and carrots in 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in chicken broth, seasonings and potatoes; simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove the bay leaf.
In skillet saute mushrooms in remaining butter 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and cream. Add to soup and bring to boil.

title: pennsylvania dutch corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add eggs to milk.
Mix liquid with corn mixture and pour into a greased casserole.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt with cold milk.
Add scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Cook slowly until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, coconut and butter.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake at 325° for 13 minutes.

title: delicious nourishing chili
directions: Brown ground beef in large pot.
Drain off fat.
In saucepan, boil potatoes and carrots until soft.
Mash potatoes and carrots together; set aside to use as thickening.
Add chopped onion, salt, chili powder, mushrooms, tomato juice, stewed tomatoes and bouillon cubes.
Add mashed potatoes and carrots.
Stir and let simmer 1 hour on low heat, stirring now and then.

title: mock apple rings
directions: First Day:
Peel and slice cucumbers and remove seeds.
Cover with lime-water solution.
Soak 24 hours.

title: easy and delicious dump cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and pour into 8 x 8-inch pan. Pour pie filling into the middle and gently spread to within 1-inch or so of the edge.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: punch
directions: Mix gelatins and Kool-Aid according to directions on packages. Combine these but do not allow them to congeal.
Add prepared lemonade and pineapple juice.
Freeze this.
When ready to serve remove from freezer and chop up.
Place in a punch bowl with ginger ale.

title: september salad
directions: Combine celery, nuts, pineapple and cheese cubes and apples.

title: elim fried chicken
directions: Place the flour, paprika, salt and pepper in a plastic bag. Shake chicken pieces in the coating mix.
Put the chicken on a well-greased cookie sheet that is lined with tinfoil.
Spoon the melted butter over each 6 or 8 pieces of chicken, depending on the size.
Bake in oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes until nice and brown, at 425° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for the remainder of the time.

title: christmas nut roll
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Mix well or until moistened.
Take the remaining graham crackers from the 3rd package and 1/3 cup of pecans, crumble in Ziploc bag until fine.
Pour onto aluminum foil and set aside.
Shape other mixture into 1 foot rolls and roll into the cracker crumbs.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 Nut Rolls.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Chop apples, celery and nuts. Add raisins. Combine brown sugar and salad dressing or mayonnaise. Pour over chopped vegetables and nuts and toss well. Chill until ready to serve.

title: ruffins fish
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place margarine in Pyrex dish and put in oven until melted and browned. Salt and pepper fish.
Place fish, flesh down, in margarine.
Cook approximately 10 minutes. Turn fish over and pour mixture of wine and lemon juice on fish. Then cover with Parmesan cheese.
Broil for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cinnamon buns(yields 300 buns)
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water; let stand for 4 to 5 minutes. Place dry ingredients (flour, dry milk, sugar and salt) in mixer bowl.
Using dough hook, blend on low speed for 2 to 3 minutes. Add oil and blend on low speed for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add water and drained pineapple; mix on low for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add dissolved yeast and mix on low speed for 2 minutes.
Knead dough on medium for 8 to 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic (may need to add a little more flour).
Place in warm area for 45 to 60 minutes (90°).
Place dough on lightly floured surface.
Combine cinnamon and 4 1/2 cups of sugar (raisins and nuts are optional). Mix well; set aside.
Roll dough into rectangle.
Lightly brush each rectangle with oil.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cinnamon-sugar mixture over rectangle.
Sprinkle raisins, nuts and dates over rectangle (optional).
Roll dough to form a long, slender roll.
Cut each roll into 1-inch thick slices.
Place on lightly oiled sheet pan in rows of 10 down and 5 across.
Place in warm area (90°) until doubled in size.
Bake until lightly browned, 18 to 20 minutes at 400° in conventional oven or 12 to 14 minutes at 350° in convection oven.
Brush lightly with melted butter while warm or make confectioners sugar glaze (optional).

title: brunswick stew
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onion and potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 30 minutes. Ready to serve.

title: french onion soup
directions: Separate onions into rings and saute in butter in Dutch oven until tender.
Add both broths to onions.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir in browning sauce.
Bring mixture to a boil and reduce heat; simmer uncovered 1 hour.
Place 4 ovenproof individual serving bowls on baking sheet.
Place one sliced and cubed French bread slices in bowl.
Ladle soup over bread and top with cheese. Broil until cheese is melted.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream
butter,
margarine, sugar and egg yolk together. Add flour
and cinnamon.
Spread on a thin cookie sheet.
Pat egg white
over
the
cookie dough.
Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut while hot.

title: pappy hall's hominy casserole
directions: Mix soup, hominy and Cheez Whiz.
Bake in greased casserole for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Put onion rings on top and bake 5 more minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: puddin-n-peaches
directions: Mix pudding as per directions, omitting 1 cup of milk.
Add juice from peaches and mix thoroughly.
Add the peaches and chill. Pudding will be ready to serve in about 5 minutes.

title: mandarin orange and pineapple salad
directions: Combine oranges, pineapple, cottage cheese, whipped topping and vanilla.
Sprinkle Jell-O over mixture and stir well.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine pecans and coconut. Sprinkle over salad.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: chicken strata casserole
directions: Add 3 slices of bread made into cubes.
Beat eggs and milk. Pour over top and let stand overnight or several hours.
Add soup over top of dish, then top with 2 slices buttered bread crumbs. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add water to make one cup. Heat to a boil.
Dissolve jello in hot liquid.
Gently stir in ginger ale.
Chill until partially set.
Blend fruit; fold into gelatin and put in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm. Prepare topping and add cheese.
Spread over gelatin.
Toast nuts in 1 tablespoon of butter at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle on top and chill.

title: easy strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pour into blender.
Add softened cream cheese (chunked).
Blend until smooth.
Pour into bowl and chill.

title: german chocolate dump cake
directions: Grease and flour oblong cake pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Line bottom of pan with coconut and pecans.
Prepare cake mix (use directions on box).
Pour cake mixture in pan over coconut and pecans.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk; spread over cake mixture. Cook as directed on cake mix box.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, chocolate and milk in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from stove and add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto foil and refrigerate until hardened.

title: football casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in shortening.
Add onions, tomatoes, catsup, steak sauce, green pepper and parsley.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni.
Season to taste.
Mix soup lightly in and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is bubbling and brown.

title: nutty noodle clusters
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Remove from stove.
Quickly stir in noodles and nuts until coated.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all well.
Cover and chill one hour or overnight.
Serve with crackers or plenty of fresh vegetables.

title: petite cherry cheesecakes
directions: Place crushed vanilla wafers in paper-lined miniature muffin cups.
Cream sugar, cream cheese, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Pour into prepared muffin cups. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Do not brown.
Top each warm cheesecake with 1 tablespoonful pie filling. Yield:
42 servings.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; put into ungreased pan.
Mix next 4 ingredients; pour over batter.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake slowly.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onions. Drain. Add tomatoes, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and macaroni to skillet. Mix well and simmer for 30 minutes. Pour into large baking dish. Pour mushroom soup over top of entire dish. Cook for 20 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle cheese over top and put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Then mix together all ingredients.

title: basic quiche
directions: Brush pie shell with beaten egg white and refrigerate. preheat oven to 375°.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain, crumble. Sprinkle over bottom of pie shell.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, nutmeg and pepper until combined, not frothy.
Sprinkle grated Swiss cheese over bacon in pie shell and pour egg mixture over all. Bake on low rack in oven for 35 to 40 minutes, just until puffy and golden.
Remove from oven and place on rack; cool for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken rococo
directions: Cut cheese into 8 equal sticks.
Cut chicken breasts in half and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place a stick of cheese on each; fold in ends, then fold in sides.
Fasten with a pick.
Dip each in beaten egg, then in crumbs.
Lay on wire rack to dry for 10 or 15 minutes.
Brown in margarine.
Dissolve chicken bouillon cube in water.
Cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Add flour, seasonings and bouillon and cook until thick. Add rice and mushrooms.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: In mixer bowl, beat together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour and pudding mix; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Fold in raisins and pecans.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Confectioners Sugar Glaze.

title: fruit punch
directions: Add fruit punch to fruit.
Top with some sherbet, then add the ginger ale for the foamy look.

title: pound cake(c & h sugar recipe)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until very fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Add about half to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and then remaining flour mixture.
Spoon batter into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Makes 1 cake.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoon size onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.

title: jena's kool-aid ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Pour into a freezeable container.
Cover and freeze until firm.

title: cheese potato puff
directions: Peel potatoes and cook until tender.
Drain and mash thoroughly.
Add butter, cheese, milk and salt.
Beat until butter and cheese are melted.
Fold in eggs and pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with a little shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until puffy and golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put into greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Very good.

title: banana fruit bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Add mashed bananas; add flour which has been mixed with soda.
Mix well. Fold in cherries, nuts and chocolate bits.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: spanakopita (spinach pie)
directions: Clean spinach.
Scald in boiling water briefly and drain it well.
Saute the scallions in 3 tablespoons of butter until soft. Add spinach, parsley, dill, salt and pepper and cook for about 5 minutes.
Place the spinach mixture in a well-greased 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle the cheese evenly over the top.

title: suspiros(sighs)
directions: Gradually add the sugar and the lemon juice to the beaten egg whites.
Cover a cookie sheet with waxed paper and drop the mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls.
Bake in a 300° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.

title: veal marsala
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a flat dish.
Dip veal in this flour mixture.

title: lo-cal ranch dressing
directions: Blend well and store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups.
One tablespoon equals 10 calories.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water until tender, cool and drain.
In serving dish, alternate layers of carrots, pepper rings and onion rings.
Beat remaining ingredients (tomato soup, salad oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce) well with beater until blended.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate. Serve chilled.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot; cook on high for 8 to 10 hours.
During last half of cooking time, remove lid and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: kool-aid slushes
directions: Dissolve ingredients in 2 cups boiling water, then add 2 cups cold water.
Mix well.
Pour into small Dixie cups or small plastic cups.
Freeze in freezer.

title: icing
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat; add vanilla and sugar.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until spins thread.
Add peanuts and cook until color of peanut brittle.
Add soda and lump of butter.
Pour into large pan and stretch or pull edges as it cools.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, onion, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Layer in a shallow pan:
